title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Beat eggs, butter, milk and spices.
Alternate bread and cheese in a floured 2-quart dish.
Pour egg mixture over all and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp, okra and rice
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
In bacon fat, cook onion and green pepper until soft.
Add chopped tomatoes and seasoning.
Add rice and simmer until rice is cooked.
Add shrimp and continue to simmer until shrimp are done. Serves 4.

title: pink velvet frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and fold in Cool Whip.
Line loaf pan with foil and pour in; freeze.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: stuffed chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place 1 slice Muenster cheese and 1/4 cup stuffing on each of 12 pieces of chicken.
Roll up tightly and secure with toothpicks. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan/Romano cheese. Pour bouillon over chicken and place Provolone on top.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: crock-pot french dip
directions: Trim excess fat from roast and place roast in crock-pot.
Add the beef broth, onion soup and beer.
Cook for 1 hour on high; turn down on low and cook for 7 hours.

title: quick main dish
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add onions, celery and bell peppers to meat mixture.
Saute until vegetables are cooked.
Add seasoning.
Stir in mixed vegetables, soup and mushrooms.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put biscuits over mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Put sauerkraut and pimentos in colander to drain.
Set aside. Chop all ingredients.
Put in bowl sauerkraut, pimentos, carrots, celery, green peppers and onions.
Mix sugar and vegetable oil in separate bowl until well combined.
Pour over other ingredients; mix well with hands until mixed thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight. Recipe can be doubled or tripled as many times as needed for one or for a large crowd.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs (one at a time).
Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: curried green beans and egg casserole
directions: Cook frozen beans as directed on package.
Put in buttered, flat casserole.
Arrange deviled egg halves on top of beans. Season eggs well and use enough mayonnaise to moisten well.

title: old black joe cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together at once.
Beat at medium speed for 2 to 3 minutes.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Frost when cool.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well until fluffy looking.
Chill. Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Also, maraschino cherries look nice, especially at Christmastime.

title: chinese almond curd
directions: Mix the water and milk in a saucepan. Sprinkle the gelatin over the mixture.
Place on low heat, stirring constantly, until the gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat. Stir in the sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons almond extract.

Pour into a square or rectangular container. Chill until firm and then slice into small pieces. Transfer the pieces into a small serving bowl. Add 1 teaspoonful of almond extract. Stir in the fruit cocktail and then refrigerate until served.

title: stripe it rich cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at temperature and time on box.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes quickly down through the cake with round handle of wooden spoon at 1-inch intervals (or use a plastic straw, using a turning motion to make large holes).

title: sausage muffins
directions: Cook sausage until browned and crumbled.
Drain well.
Reserve drippings.
Add butter to drippings to measure 1/4 cup; set aside. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in medium bowl.
Mix egg, milk and 1/4 cup reserved drippings; stir well.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Stir in cheese and sausage.
Spoon batter into paper lined muffin pans. Bake at 375° for 18 minutes.
Remove from muffin pan immediately. Makes 1 dozen.

title: basic basil tomato sauce
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion and garlic in hot oil over medium heat until tender.
Add undrained tomatoes, sugar, crushed red pepper, water and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and cook 45 minutes, stirring often until thick.
Add basil and cook 1 more minute.
Serve over pasta.

title: fruit waffle sundae
directions: Toast 2 frozen waffles in the toaster.
When done, place on a plate.
Drain the liquid from a can of your favorite fruits. Place fruits on waffles.
Add ice cream (if desired) as well as: chopped nuts, whipped cream and syrup.
Enjoy!
Serves 1.

title: chocolate pastry
directions: Combine dry ingredients with chocolate drink mix.
Gently mix in enough water to moisten dry ingredients.

title: fresh cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces and cover with lightly salted ice water (about 1 teaspoon salt per quart of water).
Serves to freshen and crisp the vegetables.
Let soak about 15 minutes while preparing the dressing.

title: mom's lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar; add boiling water, stirring constantly, cook until clear.
Add butter, beaten egg yolks, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into baked pie shell; cover with meringue made from egg whites and brown slightly.

title: all-righta-potato
directions: Butter a 10 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Layer Tater Tots in dish.
Mix cream cheese and Ro-Tel together.
Place on top of Tater Tots.
Add second package of Tater Tots.
Top with cheese. Bake 30 minutes.

title: marinade for fowl
directions: Combine and pour over fowl.
Marinate 1 hour.
Grill 45 minutes.
Turn frequently and baste often.	Makes enough for 4 to 5 pounds.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in microwave.
Mix other ingredients together. Bake for 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: snacks
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together in a large roaster.
Melt butter, bacon grease and seasonings together in a saucepan; pour over mixture in the roaster and stir well.
Heat 1 hour in a 200° oven, stirring often.

title: lo-cal party dip
directions: Mix dressing and cottage cheese together.
Sprinkle with chives.

title: coq au vin(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Remove bacon and cut into squares.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Rinse in cold water; dry.
In electric skillet, saute bacon slowly in 2 tablespoons butter.
Dry chicken and brown thoroughly.
Add bacon pieces and season with salt and pepper.
Add cognac and ignite, shaking pan to coat chicken.
Add Burgundy, chicken stock, tomato paste, garlic, thyme and bay leaf.
Cook rapidly until liquid is about 2 1/4 cups.
Blend flour and 2 tablespoons butter. Beat into liquid and stir until thickened.
While chicken is cooking, prepare the following.

title: italian dream cake
directions: Cream the oleo and shortening.
Add sugar, beating until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: tofu pumpkin pie
directions: Process all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: overnight sticky buns
directions: Pour melted butter or margarine over buns.
Combine brown sugar and pudding.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Top with chopped nuts. Cover pan lightly with towel and refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt and sugar.
Add and cut in shortening.
Add half and half.
Add boiling water.
Fry in hot skillet with at least 1/2-inch of shortening or oil.
I drop from teaspoon; it turns out so good!

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add other ingredients in order listed until cream cheese and mayonnaise are no longer lumpy.
Pour into a mold; chill until firm.

title: spinach dip(allison deerson)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Microwave on Medium (50%) for 9 to 12 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes until Cheddar cheese melts and mixture is warm. Serve warm with bread.

title: noodles
directions: Put flour in a large bowl.
Add the liquid mixture.
Mix slightly with a fork and then with the hand.
This makes a large amount.
For the turkey supper, I make about 100 pounds.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Chop fruit and nuts.
Use 1 cup of flour to dredge; mix as usual.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, eggs, etc.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Add more dressing, if needed.
Chill again.
Toss and serve.

title: rich and moist chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix everything thoroughly, except chocolate chips, fold these in last.
Put in greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
When cake is cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, and one egg together.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan.
Beat 3 eggs, then add cream cheese, beat well, then add
powdered sugar, and vanilla.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: corned beef cabbage skillet
directions: Remove outside leaves from cabbage; wash cabbage.
Coarsely shred to measure 3 cups.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Stir in cabbage, hash browns, water and salt.
Cook uncovered over medium-high heat until liquid is absorbed and bottom is brown, 8 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetables in wine
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add cauliflower, peas, carrots, celery and onion.
Combine bouillon cube with wine, salt and black pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Cook quickly over high heat about 10 minutes, stirring constantly, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add almonds, if used.
Stir.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: the dream student recipe
directions: Teachers give this to your class, it will become your dream class.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Put cooked and drained vegetables in casserole dish.
Mix together rest of the ingredients and put on top of vegetables. Bake at 300°
for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: fruit medley punch
directions: Prepare Ice Ring in advance if desired.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients for 1 to 2 minutes. Pour into 2 buttered loaf pans lined with waxed paper. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Check for doneness. Cook a little longer if necessary. Let cool. Remove from pans before completely cool and top with Glaze.

title: tuna vegetable rabbit
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: easy gourmet chicken
directions: Pound chicken and put in large shallow baking dish.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Mix them with sour cream, soup and sherry. Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate lush
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix together flour, pecans and melted butter or oleo; pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Simmer spaghetti sauce in a large frying pan. Add next 7 ingredients plus chicken.
Meanwhile, cook and drain noodles according to package directions.
Add noodles to sauce and blend well. Serve with Parmesan cheese sprinkled over top.

title: irene's cheesecake
directions: Make graham cracker crust with crackers and margarine.
Press firmly into 7 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Add Jell-O and blend.
Fold in stiffly beaten Milnot milk.
(This is done with electric mixer.) Add filling to crust and sprinkle with finely chopped pecans. Chill overnight.
Keeps well.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: chocolate fudge icing
directions: Melt margarine and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for one minute.
Remove from heat and beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Tastes like homemade fudge.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine margarine, eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and salt. Gently add pecans and mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir gently and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: hobo supper
directions: Place potatoes from mix in large saucepan.
Reserve sauce mix packet.
Add water to cover potato slices and boil for 7 minutes; drain.
Combine ground beef, garlic salt and pepper; blend well. Shape in patties.
Place each patty on a sheet of heavy foil, then top with potatoes and mixed vegetables.
Mix sauce mix with 1/2 cup of water.
Spoon over potatoes and vegetables.
Securely wrap each packet.
Cook in oven for 40 minutes at 350° or on a grill for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until it comes off the bone easily.
Save broth. Put broken up chicken in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Remove fat from broth.
Add bouillon cube.
Make a thin gravy with cornstarch. Pour over chicken until it just covers.
Make Bisquick rolled biscuits and place on top of chicken and gravy.
Cook according to directions or until done.

title: oatmeal icebox cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugars.
Beat eggs and add to sugar.
Add the flour, soda, and salt.
Then add the vanilla, oatmeal and nuts or chips.
Mix well and make long rolls.
Refrigerate overnight, cut and bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.

title: caramel delights
directions: Spread caramels over bottom of saucepan; add cream.
Melt caramels with switch turned to lowest heat position, stirring occasionally, until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased baking sheet or waxed paper.
(Caramels can be melted in microwave.)

title: ice cream pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add vanilla ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until ice cream is melted.
Add fruit (optional).
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Chill until set.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Press this on a cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 400°. Crumble while warm.
Put 1/2 crumb mixture in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Drizzle 1/2 jar of caramel ice cream topping over top. Spread 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream that is softened slightly. Put remaining crumb mixture over ice cream.
Drizzle remaining caramel topping over crumbs.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Best done 24 hours ahead.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Salt and pepper the chicken strips.
Cook on medium-high heat for 3 minutes on each side.
Set aside.
Prepare stir-fry as directed.
Add chicken to stir-fry; toss 30 seconds and enjoy.

title: hot slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat to boiling.
Boil on heat about 20 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Put in jars.
(Makes 9 pints.)

title: lemon cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine, sugar and egg together; mix well.
Stir in flour, lemon extract and nuts; mix well.
Shape into walnut-size balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten to about 1/8-inch round.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: peach pie
directions: Slice peaches into pie shell.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add sour cream.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: tuna and pepper fricassee
directions: Preparation:
10 minutes.
Cooking:
20 minutes.
Heat the vegetable oil in a heavy skillet and cook the tuna pieces for 2 minutes per side, turning once.
Transfer the tuna to a platter and keep warm.
Add the peppers to the oil and cook until softened, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes.
Return the tuna pieces to the pan and season with cayenne pepper and salt to taste.
Cover the pan and cook for 5 minutes longer.
Serves six.

title: corn relish
directions: Use large saucepan (8 quarts).
Cut corn from cobs, scraping the ears, making about 4 cups.
Mix corn with the chopped vegetables.
Place all vegetables in large pan and add all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer the relish over low heat, stirring occasionally, until fairly thick, about 30 minutes.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Yields 6 1/2 pints.

title: cabbage unrolled
directions: Place 1/3 of cabbage in a large dutch oven.
In a bowl, combine beef, rice, onion, salt and pepper; form into meatballs.
Place half of the meatballs on top of the cabbage.
Cover with 1/3 of the cabbage and the rest of the meatballs.
Top with the remaining 1/3 of the cabbage.
Pour tomato puree and beef broth over all.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered 20 minutes, or until meat is cooked through.

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Add chopped onion to ground chuck and cook until no pink is left. Drain well. Season with salt and pepper and place in the bottom of a casserole dish. Cover with sliced carrots and then potatoes. Mix soup with enough water to make 2 cups. Pour over the potatoes. Cover and bake at 350 until potatoes are done, approximately 35-40 minutes.

title: zucchini scallop
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Place in buttered baking dish and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger-cheese bake
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Meanwhile, cook noodles and drain.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows and peanut butter.
Pour in 10 x 7 or 8-inch pan.

title: moist oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray cookie sheet with cooking spray.
In large bowl, mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In separate bowl, whisk together shortening, applesauce, granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Fold in oats and raisins.
Add flour mixture; stir well.

title: freezer jam
directions: Mash berries; add sugar and mix.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup pectin and water.
Bring to boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 1 minute; add to berries.
Stir constantly for 3 minutes.
Ladle into jar or container.
Let sit for 24 hours prior to freezing.

title: cocktail pizzas
directions: Brown meats.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add seasoning and meat mixture to cheese.
Put on bread while warm.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
(Freezable, don't bake before you freeze.)

title: splatter-proof meat balls
directions: Line broiler pan with aluminum foil.
Spray broiler rack with nonstick spray.
Roll meat balls and line along grooves of broiler rack.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: creamy hash browns
directions: In a greased 13 x 9 baking dish, place the patties. Sprinkle with salt and garlic powder. Pour cream over patties and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes. Sprinkle on the cheese; bake 10 minutes longer, until cheese is melted and potatoes are tender.

title: candied sweet potatoes with dates and pecans
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch slices; peel slices and cut each into quarters.
Saute potatoes in butter in a large, heavy skillet 15 minutes over medium heat.
Add next 5 ingredients; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add dates; recover and cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Transfer to a serving dish; stir in pecans.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: dropped tea cakes
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop dough by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: salsa
directions: All ingredients are to personal taste.
Adjust accordingly.

title: frozen lemon custard
directions: Combine in
top of double boiler and cook for 3 minutes over boiling water, stirring constantly.
Add juice of 1 large lemon. Stir
until well blended and set aside to cool.
While cooling, beat
2 egg whites and 1 tablespoon sugar until stiff and glossy. Fold
in
1/2 pint whipping cream slowly and then the
cooled
egg mixture.
Crush
vanilla
wafers.
Cover bottom
of 8-inch square pan with crumbs, reserving about 1/3. Pour
filling	over crumbs and sprinkle remaining crumbs over the top.	Freeze	for
6 to 8 hours.
Cut in squares to serve and decorate with fresh strawberries or peaches.

title: frozen punch
directions: Add everything together except ginger ale with enough water to fill container, leaving space for ginger ale.
Freeze for 24 hours or until slush.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add soup, cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve with noodles.

title: caramel cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in 9-inch x 13-inch pan. When done, pike holes with fork and pour condensed milk over top of cake.
Allow to set while beating caramel topping in microwave (1 minute).
Pour over hot cake.
Let cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: rice from bogota
directions: Cut chicken and marinate in garlic, salt, lime and orange juice, onions and pepper.
Let stand for at least 1 hour.
In large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Add marinated mixture and cook for 15 minutes.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover and cook for about 1 hour over low heat.
Cool.
Remove bones and cut chicken into small pieces.
Return to sauce.
Mix milk, Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and wine.
Add to chicken.
Cook rice.
Combine cooked rice and chicken mixture in bowl.
Add raisins, capers and sliced olives. Place mixture into 2 oblong baking dishes.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until well heated.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in vinegar; mix well.
Add sugar and cook until clear and thick.
Add Tabasco, Worcestershire, soy sauce, mustard, peppers and pineapple.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Use with meatballs, hot dogs, shrimp, etc.

title: crab spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, garlic and parsley in oil. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and seasonings. Simmer 2 to 3 hours. Add crab and wine and simmer 10 minutes. Take cooked pasta (drain, but don't rinse) add sauce and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken and rice in a casserole dish and pour the remaining ingredients over chicken.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican buildup
directions: Crumble beef into heated skillet.
Cook until meat loses color. Add chopped onion during last few minutes cooking time.
Drain grease.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce with mushrooms and water; simmer for 15 or 20 minutes.
Cook the egg noodles.
Drain.
Mix cream cheese, soup and sour cream. Heat.
Put half the meat in buttered casserole dish.
Put noodles over meat.
Put cream cheese, sour cream and mushroom soup over noodles.
Top with remaining meat.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice for 5 minutes in water and salt listed.
Then combine with rest of ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator pistachio dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, mix flour and butter until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until golden brown and cool. In small bowl, combine cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth and creamy.
Fold in 1/2 carton of Cool Whip; spread over cool crust.
In a medium bowl, combine pudding mix and milk.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour over cheese layer.
Frost with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: stuffed shells
directions: You can add 1 pound ground beef or 8 ounces mushrooms to sauce.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, stir together all ingredients.
Stir frequently. Bring to boil; reduce heat and boil gently 15 minutes to thicken. Makes 2 cups.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Saute together onion and celery.
Cook separately rice and frozen chopped broccoli.
Mix vegetables and add soups and Cheez Whiz.
Place rice in greased casserole and pour mixture over it. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Can be prepared ahead of time and baked just before ready to eat.

title: pink punch
directions: In medium size punch bowl, put lemonade.
Do not dilute. Leave as it comes from the can.
Add thawed strawberries and then the ginger ale.
Serve in 6 ounce punch cups.

title: graham cracker cookies(no bake)
directions: Use shallow 11 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with layer of crackers.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar.
Beat egg in the 1/2 cup of milk.
Add mixture.
Bring to boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Continue to stir.
Remove from heat.
Add the 1 cup of crumbs plus coconut.
Spread on crackers.
Add another layer of crackers on top.
Makes a sandwich effect.

title: bugle horns
directions: Fill Bugles with peanut butter using a knife or pipe in with a pastry bag.
Dip Bugles in melted chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: pecan pumpkin pie
directions: Spread	over
bottom
of uncooked pie crust, then cover with Pecan Mixture.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: rancher's skillet
directions: In skillet, brown hot dogs and cook onions and garlic in butter until onions are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat; stir now and then.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake for about 30 minutes.

title: layered beans and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions and green pepper in butter.
Stir in garlic and beans.
In another pan, bring wine and bay leaf to a boil.
Stir in tomato paste.
Layer bean mixture, sausage and rice in a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Salt, if desired, and pepper each layer.
Remove bay leaf; pour wine mixture over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Uncover; bake 20 minutes longer.

title: honey chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and measure; add soda and salt and sift together 3 times.
Cream shortening, gradually add honey, beating well after each addition to keep mixture thick.
Add 1/4 of flour mixture and beat until smooth and well blended.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in chocolate and blend.
Add remaining flour alternately with water, beating very well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 2 greased 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Frost and fill with Quick Creamed Frosting.

title: honey mustard dip
directions: Blend ingredients.
Serve with chicken nuggets, ham or cheese cubes, pretzels or bread sticks.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Measure
flour,
sugar,
cereal
and baking powder into mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Drop by tablespoon
onto an ungreased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric together.
Add cucumber and onion.
Microwave 7 to 8 minutes, stirring twice.
Put in quart jar and cover; let cool. Store in fridge.

title: date nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix dates and nuts.
Add flour mixture and date mixture; stir with a fork.
Add milk mixture and stir until just moistened.
Do not beat!
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Serve hot.
Good with hot cereal.

title: dilled split pea soup
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp; remove bacon to absorbent paper to drain and reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add peas to boiling water in a medium-sized saucepan; add salt, bacon drippings and onion.
Cover and boil gently for 1 hour, adding more water during cooking process (about 1 cup water will be needed).
Add dill weed; cover saucepan and cook over very low heat 1/2 hour longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in evaporated milk and cayenne pepper; heat to serving temperature.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle on top of each serving.
Serves about 4.

title: sister sarah's gingered chicken
directions: Poach chicken in enough broth to cover pieces until chicken is barely done.
Remove and discard skin and bones.
Cut meat into large chunks and set aside.
Reserve broth.
Peel pears and cut into quarters if large, halves if very small.
Core pears. Combine juice concentrate, reserved broth and ginger in skillet. Add pears and poach for 5 minutes.
Add chicken and cook until pears are just barely cooked through and chicken is hot.
Serve over rice.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove and spread 1/4 cup barbecue sauce on top and bake another 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Fold together in a large bowl;
refrigerate.

title: cool veggie pizza appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Press dough onto bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown; cool.
Mix cream cheese, salad dressing, dill and onion salt until well blended.
Spread on crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: orange sauce
directions: Peel oranges; chop them fine and remove the seeds.
Add half a peeled lemon and the sugar.
Mix well; spread between the layers of short cake or spread over angel food cake.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in halves lengthwise.
Place in casserole dish. Pour tomatoes over squash.
Sprinkle on green pepper and place onion slices on top.
Season with salt and pepper; dot with butter.
Cover and bake.

title: peanut butter microwave fudge
directions: Melt butter in microwave in a large bowl. Add powdered sugar and milk. Cook in microwave for 3 minutes. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Pour into pan.

title: crispy oat cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugars; mix well.
Add egg; beat well.
Add oil and vanilla; mix.
Combine flour, salt and soda; add to mix and stir well.
Stir in other ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets; flatten top of ball with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 dozen.

title: old fashion chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Take chicken apart; cut fine pieces. Take the rest of the ingredients into pan.
Cook until carrots are done.
Cover and simmer for at least 2 hours.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Brown together the bacon, hamburger and onion.
While cooking, mix together the remaining ingredients.
Mix all together in a large baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil, bone and cut up chicken.
Mix milk, soup, chicken, peas and onions.
Melt butter, pour over stuffing mix. Put 1/2 stuffing in casserole, pour chicken mix over top with rest of stuffing. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: best ever challah
directions: Mix water and yeast in large Mixmaster bowl.
Add 2 cups bread and 1 cup regular flour and 1 cup sugar.
Stir with fork and let rise for 1/2 hour in warm place.
Meanwhile, in another bowl, measure in 4 cups bread flour and 1 cup regular, 1 tablespoon salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add margarine and cut in with knife until mixture resembles coarse meal.
At the end of half hour, add 4 beaten eggs to yeast mixture (mix will decrease in volume).
Add flour, margarine mixture and raisins to mixer bowl.
Use bread hook until all flour is mixed.

title: herby hamburgers
directions: Combine ingredients and form into 4 to 6 patties.
Brown on both sides in lightly oiled skillet.
Mix mushroom soup with milk. Pour over hamburger patties and cook over low to medium heat. This makes its own thickened gravy and is great with mashed potatoes.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Cook macaroni for 12 minutes.
While the macaroni is cooking, combine the soup, milk and pimentos, then add salmon (flaked) and liquid, part of cheese, bread crumbs and macaroni.
Mix well, then pour into well-greased casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and bread crumbs over top.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruitcake
directions: Mix butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 3 hours.
Put a pan of water under rack.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix cornmeal to a paste in salted water.
Gradually stir it into boiling water.
Cover and cook slowly for 20 minutes. Combine tomato sauce with cooked meat.
Stir in seasonings.
In casserole dish, arrange layers of cornmeal mush and beef and tomato mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cajunized oriental pork chops
directions: Salt and red pepper the chops.
Brown them slowly in a skillet.
Add wine, bell pepper, onion and garlic.
Cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove pork chops, being sure to keep them warm.
Add the soy sauce and syrup from the pineapple. Stir until more or less thick.
Add the pineapple chunks and bring to a boil.
Serve over pork chops and hot cooked rice.
Makes six servings.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook
noodles
according
to package directions; drain. Add oregano and
ground beef to sauce.
In 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish,
layer as follows:
1/2 noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sauce; repeat for second layer.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crumbs) well.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over the top of the mix and bake for about 40 minutes at 375°.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together by hand and press evenly into a greased 9 x 10-inch pan.
Press chocolate chips on top of cake mix mixture.
Mix egg, powdered sugar and cream cheese together with a mixer.
Spread evenly over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach roll
directions: Saute 2 tablespoons butter and onions.
Add dill and parsley and saute 5 minutes.
Cook spinach, drain and cool.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add to butter and onions.
Beat eggs.
Add cheeses.
Mix together.
Make pie dough and roll thin.
Brush with rest of melted butter.
Spread spinach mixture on dough and roll in jelly roll fashion.
Place on flat cookie sheet.
Pierce dough with fork.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Slice.
Can be made ahead and reheated.

title: rich chocolate chip toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, stir flour and brown sugar together.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips and nuts.
Reserved 1 1/2 cups mixture.
Press remaining crumb mixture onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over hot crust; top with 1 1/2 cups toffee bits.
Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture and remaining 1/2 cup chips over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with remaining toffee bits.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars.

title: plain waffles
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Drop in egg yolks and gradually add milk, beating until batter is smooth. Beat in the melted butter.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in 3 minutes waffle iron which has been preheated 10 minutes. Will make 5 waffles.

title: swiss bliss(a meal in one pan)
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, put 20-inch strip of heavy-duty foil.
Grease with oleo.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt about 11 ounces of candy bars and 1 stick of margarine in double boiler until smooth, set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick of margarine, add eggs 1 at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour, buttermilk and soda.
Add Milky Way mixture, vanilla and nuts. Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: crunch snacks
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 250°.

title: cream cheese cookie
directions: Cream together sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Add egg, vanilla and flour.
Put on cookie sheet and top with nuts or cherries.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: eggplant dip
directions: Slit eggplant skin with a sharp knife.
Place over foil on cookie sheet.
Broil, turning twice until skin is burnt and blistered.
It should have a smoky smell, about 20 minutes.
Inside of eggplant should be very soft now.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Cut out skin and scoop eggplant meat into a serving bowl. Mash with a fork and add all other ingredients.
Serve with grilled pita bread triangles.

title: king's arms tavern corn relish(4 servings)
directions: Drain all of the ingredients well.
Mix the ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill before serving.

title: chewy peanut butter bars
directions: Cream butter, sugars and peanut butter until fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture and blend.
Stir in coconut. Spread dough into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: pretzel jello dessert
directions: Mix pretzels and margarine together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sugar. Add Dream Whip (mix according to package directions).
Spread over pretzels.
Mix jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Pour over cheese layer after jello starts to set.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a pie pan and spread hash browns on bottom, then brush with melted butter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Then layer ham, chilies, and cheese.
Beat eggs, add milk, salt and pour over above.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place salsa on top when serving.

title: italian sausage spinach pie
directions: In a skillet brown sausage and onion until the sausage is done and onion is tender.
Drain.

title: onion hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil, stir until smooth.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls into deep, hot oil (350°); cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry 1 to 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl with mayonnaise.
Ready to serve with saltines.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rice pudding
directions: Break eggs into the baking dish (1 1/2-quart size).
Mix in sugar.
Add milk, vanilla, rice and raisins.
Mix.
Place several slices of bread on top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie pan 2/3 full of apples.
Mix and sprinkle sugar and cinnamon onto apples. Mix together the remaining ingredients. Pour batter over apples.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Strain tuna, then add the egg, bread crumbs and seasonings. Mix all ingredients.
Shape into burgers.
Cook on a nonstick pan 3 minutes on each side and then top with cheese! Ready to eat!

title: banana cream custard pie
directions: Combine the milk, egg yolks, sugar, salt and cornstarch and cook over low heat. Bring to a boil. Add the cream cheese and stir until the cheese is melted. Remove the mixture from the heat and add nuts, vanilla and butter. Stir until well mixed. Cool for 20 to 30 minutes. Place a sheet of plastic wrap on top of the cooling pot to help avoid a crust from forming on the custard. Place the sliced bananas on the bottom of the pie crust and top with the cooled custard. Sprinkle with coconut and refrigerate.

title: date balls
directions: Cook oleo, sugar and chopped dates until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Cool.
Make into balls and lightly roll in powdered sugar.

title: hash brown hash(microwave easy)
directions: Note:
Pepper wedges are used for serving dishes for the hash.

title: emergency pickles
directions: Chop all peppers.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook slow until vegetables are tender, but not soft.
Hot pack in hot jars and seal.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add crushed pineapple. Beat together whipped cream and cream cheese; blend together with gelatin mixture.
Stir in miniature marshmallows and chopped nut meats.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine; combine all the ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: russian chicken
directions: Combine dressing, preserves and onion soup mix.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: pasta pizza venison bake
directions: Cook macaroni and drain; in large skillet, cook the venison with salt and pepper.
Drain if necessary.
Place half of macaroni in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with half of the venison, pizza sauce, mushrooms and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: tomato soup
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients
together until tender. Strain our juice. Melt margarine. Add flour, sugar, salt and pepper. Pour juice into pot. Add thicken. Let come to good boil. Put in jar and seal.

title: dibba's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except catsup.
Place mixture into a loaf pan.
Spread catsup on top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan squares
directions: Blend together until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press firmly and evenly into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Chop into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Mix all other ingredients in.
Put stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: linda's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan. Stir and heat just to boiling.
Cool and bottle.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve cubes in water; add Jell-O.
Blend mayo and cheese. Add Jell-O mixture; add the rest of ingredients and mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill overnight.
Cut in squares and garnish.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oleo; let cool.
Add marshmallows and pecans; mix well.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on wax paper.
Pour mixture onto powdered sugar; roll in sugar and shape in roll. Wrap in wax paper.
Chill for several hours, then slice.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces; fry.
Cook bacon until crisp. Remove from grease and cook diced onions until tender.
Mix with beans, sugar and catsup.
Put into a baking dish; bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sausage spins
directions: Make biscuit dough according to directions on Bisquick box. Roll dough out into a rectangle 1/3-inch thick.
Crumble uncooked sausage over dough.
Roll up as for a jelly roll and seal edges (at this point sausage rolls can be wrapped and frozen).
Slice into pinwheels and bake at 450° on ungreased cookie sheet until sizzling and brown.
Serve hot (easy to slice if refrigerated first).
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: cheese and cream potatoes
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Lay potatoes.
Microwave potatoes until almost cooked.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake until nicely brown (about 40 minutes) at 325° or 350°.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt, sugar, vanilla and melted margarine.
Add cocoa, flour and pecans.
Pour into greased square pan and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting. Should be slightly chewy.

title: ingrid's chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pesto pinwheels
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thick. Spread each piece with pesto sauce. Roll up jelly roll fashion and secure each piece with a toothpick. Dredge in bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Slice and serve.

title: toasted pecan cake
directions: Toast pecans in 1/4 cup margarine in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cheese.
Mix well.
Add flour and seasoning, then rice puffs.
Form and shape into balls.
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° until golden brown, approximately 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients well.
Put spoonfuls into individual foil squares.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sweet and sour venison
directions: Braise ribs or stew meat chunks in a little oil until brown. Add water, raisins and salt and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cut up peppers in strips and lay over meat.
Add vinegar, sugar, pineapple and cornstarch.
Simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.
When done, add several dashes of soy sauce before serving on rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form ball.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and form into ball. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: landfill cake
directions: Grease cake pan.
Pour pineapple and pie filling in cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix (dry) over top.
Sprinkle nuts (if using) over top.
Place butter patties all over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Put all ingredients in pan except hamburger. Crumble raw hamburger on top; salt and pepper. Cook for 1 hour.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add apples and nuts; mix well.
Spread butter in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, salt and eggs.
Pour in milk.
Cook until mixture coats pan.
Cool.
Stir in and add cream and vanilla.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: impossible brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease pie pan, 9 x 1 1/4-inches. Beat all ingredients, except nuts, until smooth, 2 minutes on high. Pour in plate; sprinkle with nuts. Bake until knife comes out clean, about 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Serve with ice cream.

title: turnip green casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fried pies
directions: In a pot, combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Stir in milk and margarine.	Cook
and
stir
until	bubbly.
Cook
1 more minute. Add
vanilla and cool.
Combine biscuit mix and milk; mix
well. Roll
dough
1/2-inch
thick
and
cut 10 (4-inch) circles.
Place 1 tablespoon filling on each circle; fold over and press
edges. Heat
oil
to
375° in frying pan.	Fry and brown on both sides. Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: irish creme
directions: Mix well in blender.
Store in refrigerator.

title: garden slaw
directions: Mix shredded cabbage, carrots, onion and green pepper. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup water; chill.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt and pepper in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Stir in softened gelatin, cool until slightly thickened; beat well.
Gradually beat in salad oil.

title: salsa!
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add onions and saute until clear.
Add sweet pepper and jalapeno peppers; saute until soft.
Add cumin, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes; stir well.
Add wine and cilantro. Simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Makes about 2 pints or 1 quart.
In larger quantities salsa may be canned by the hot water bath method. Enjoy!

title: lemon pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients with fork.
Do not use electric mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Let cheese get to room temperature.
Mix everything together. Separate into 3 balls.
Sprinkle with paprika on wax paper and roll into 3 logs.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.
Slice and serve on tray surrounded by crackers and olives.

title: candied citrus peel
directions: Score the fruit with sharp knife into lengthwise sections. Remove from fruit; leave on white pith.
Place in saucepan; cover with water and bring to boil.
Remove from heat; let stand 10 minutes and drain.
Repeat process 3 times.
Cool and cut peel into 1/8 to 1/4-inch wide strips.
Put sugar and water in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add peel; cook over medium heat 20 to 25 minutes, until peel is translucent.
Drain; cool and roll in sugar.
Dry on racks 48 hours.
Store in airtight containers.

title: laura's chocolate cake
directions: Bake the cake per package directions in 2 (9-inch) round pans. While cake is baking, make frosting.

title: cream of mushroom chicken
directions: Slice mushrooms and saute in butter in small pan; set aside. Place chicken in lightly greased frying pan and brown slightly on medium-high temperature.
Reduce heat to medium and add both cans of soup, water, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Let it simmer, covered up, for 10 to 20 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Makes 4 servings.
This is best served over white rice.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except pasta.
Cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Add pasta; cook 15 minutes more.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when serving.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Mix well.
Make into balls.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Put 10x sugar into a bag; shake the puffs in the sugar.

title: sour cream noodles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles; drain.
Combine with all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Spoon into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix these ingredients together.
Beat batter until butter is all beaten into batter.
Pour this batter over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: macaroni and cheese(not for the faint of heart)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350.
Lightly butter a deep 2 1/2 quart casserole.

title: hot artichoke cheese squares
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Beat eggs and mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Pour mixture into buttered 11 x 17 x 1 pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until set.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Steam
(or
cook
and
drain)
cabbage 8 to 10 minutes. Combine beef, onion and pepper and cook over medium heat until beef
is
brown
and
vegetables
are tender; drain well.
Add paste,
sauce and spices; mix well. Spoon half of cabbage into greased baking dish (12 x 9 x 2-inch). Cover with half of meat mixture;
repeat.
Cover
and
bake
at
for 25 minutes. Uncover
and
sprinkle
with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer. (Delicious with cornbread.)

title: oatmeal raisin refrigerator cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg; set aside.
Cream butter or margarine and sugars.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture, oats, raisins and nuts just until blended.
Shape into 2 (10-inch) rolls.
(If dough is too soft, chill slightly before rolling.)
Wrap in waxed paper and then with aluminum foil.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesy beer and veggie soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine bag of vegetables, potatoes, bouillon, onions and butter. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas and buttermilk. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture, a small amount at a time; mix until smooth.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased pans.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana chunks
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Dip bananas in melted mix.
Roll in crushed candy.
Freeze.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk. Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Boil 2 1/2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate morsels until melted. Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla. Dip into a 9 x 13 pan or clear dish; wait until cool and cut into squares.

title: my man's cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Beat in egg.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Blend in oatmeal, coconut and nutmeats.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. You can always double the recipe and freeze some.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Take a 9 x 13-inch pan and grease.
Put a layer of bread, then smokey links, then cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Beat slightly.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove and uncover 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing until well blended.
Add chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 5 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: presbyterian casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup noodles in large bowl; mix well.
Top with reserve noodles.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes longer until browned. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream of ramp soup
directions: Melt butter in a deep pan.
Add ramps; saute for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and garlic, stirring 1 to 2 minutes.
Gradually stir in chicken stock.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in milk and cream; heat but do not boil.
Serve with croutons and grated Monterey Jack cheese.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes. Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: veggie roll-ups
directions: Mix together cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle veggies on, roll up tight and slice.

title: buckeye bars
directions: Combine margarine and 1 cup of peanut butter in a mixing bowl. Beat until fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar and continue to beat well until mixed together completely.
Pat mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: apple dumpling cobbler
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and separate.
Wrap each apple quarter with roll dough and place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Bring orange juice, 2/3 c sugar and butter to a boil in a saucepan.
Pour over apple dumplings.
Stir together 2 tsp sugar and 1 tsp cinnamon-sprinkle over dumplings.
Bake at 350 degree oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden and bubbly.
Very good and delicious.

title: sweet and sour pork(microwave)
directions: In a small bowl, combine reserved syrup, vinegar and cornstarch.
Cook at High 3/4 to 1 minute or until thickened. Stir once.
Place oil in an 8-inch square dish.
Cook at High for 2 minutes; stir in pork, soy sauce and onions.
Cook at High for 7 to 8 minutes.
Add green pepper and pineapple.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook at High 2 to 3 minutes or until pork is tender.
Stir in sauce.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: foolproof chocolate icing
directions: Combine and cook in a double boiler, stirring constantly, until thick.

title: salmon soup
directions: Heat milk in double boiler to boiling point. Put in salmon that has been shredded with a fork. When milk is hot, thicken with cracker crumbs or serve with soup crackers.

title: mixed meat and vegetable dish
directions: Season with salt and pepper.
Mix well and put in baking dish (large).
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake around 30 minutes at 350°.

title: western hero sandwich
directions: In a large skillet, heat butter and saute garlic, onion and green pepper for 5 minutes.
Stir in pimento.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper.
Pour eggs evenly over vegetables in skillet and stir until eggs are scrambled.
Spoon eggs onto bottom of hero loaves. Top with tomato slices and grated cheese. Replace top and serve hot with mixed pickles and carrot sticks.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in greased pan for 25 minutes.
A glass 9 x 13-inch dish is best to use.

title: christmas morning coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together over nuts and raisins.
Coat well.
Add creamed mixture and sour cream.

title: frozen suckers
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, jello and sugar.
To 6 tablespoons of the dry mixture, add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Pour into molds and freeze.
Makes 6 popsicles.

title: orange-cranberry sauce
directions: Combine sugar, orange juice and water in a large saucepan. Bring to boil over medium-low heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Add berries and cook until popped, 5 to 7 minutes. Mash some of the berries with the back of the spoon. Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Cool completely.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sweet potatoes and black beans
directions: Place sweet potatoes in 2 quart saucepan; add enough water just to cover sweet potatoes. Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until tender; drain and set aside. Mix orange juice, cornstarch, pie spice and cumin in same saucepan. Heat to boiling. Boil about 1 minute, stirring constantly, until thickened. Stir in sweet potatoes, beans and rice. Cook about 2 minutes or until hot.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell as directed; set aside.
In medium saucepan stir together 2 c. raspberries, 3/4 c. sugar, cold water, lemon juice, and cornstarch.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly; cook and stir for 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Carefully fold 2 c. of the remaining raspberries into the chilled mixture, spoon in to pastry shell.
Cover; chill for at least 2 hours or until firm.

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: Place cream cheese on a serving platter.
Pour over cocktail sauce.
Top with salad shrimp. Garnish with green onion. Squeeze about 1 teaspoon lemon juice and 1 teaspoon parsley flakes over top.
Serve with fancy crackers.

title: my mother's green goddess salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.
Dilute to desired consistency with milk, cream or buttermilk.

title: molasses pie
directions: Beat whole eggs together; add sugar, flour and cream.
Lastly, add sorghum molasses, butter and vanilla.
Pour in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake in slow oven at 325° until done, approximately 45 minutes.
Halve ingredients for 1 pie.

title: hash browns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a baking pan, cover bottom of pan with potatoes.
Mix sour cream, onions and cheese together and place on top of the potatoes.
Then add melted oleo and crumbled corn flakes.
Cover and bake in oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover for last 15 minutes.

title: sour cream enchilada
directions: Combine 1 can cream of chicken soup, 1 can diced Ortega chili peppers and sour cream.
Pour half of mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Grate Jack cheese, Cheddar cheese, fill corn tortillas with cooked hamburger, green onions and half of the cheese mixture.
Put in pan, top with remainder of hamburger. Pour remaining sauce mix over the top.
Then put the rest of the cheese and onions on the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine salt and pepper with lemon rind and sweet potatoes in a large mixing bowl; roll mixture into 8 equal-sized balls. Put 1 marshmallow into the center of each ball.
Place crumbs in a large mixing bowl; roll balls in crumbs.
Combine the egg and water in a small mixing bowl; dip the balls into this and roll again in crumbs.
Pour 2 inches of vegetable oil into large skillet and heat.
Fry balls for about 4 minutes, or until brown and crispy.
Drain on paper towels.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Clean leeks and cut into 1/2-inch squares.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Cut bacon small and fry over moderate heat. Melt butter.
Add veggies and saute about 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth and season to taste. Cover pan and simmer about 30 minutes. Add the milk, a little at a time.
(Do not boil.)
Stir in parsley.
Add grated cheese.
Serves 4.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Chop
wafers, nuts and mixed fruit, then add milk.
Put on wax paper and roll in a long roll.
Sift powdered sugar and roll. Refrigerate.
Makes 2 rolls.
When cold, slice.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: After peeling and cubing potatoes, generously sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: apple crunch
directions: Slice enough apples to fill 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup water to apples and sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over top.
Mix together 1 cup sugar, flour, baking soda and egg.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° to 400° degrees until golden brown.
Top with Vanilla Sauce.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Combine rice, mushroom soup, broccoli and Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° to 400° until it bubbles, about 20 minutes.

title: cottage fries
directions: Bake on grill or in oven.
Use 3 layers of aluminum foil to seal around potatoes.
Cut potatoes like cottage fries and mix with butter, onions and seasonings.
Cook until tender, approximately 30 minutes in sealed layers of foil.
After cooked, open layers of foil and cover with cheese.
Serve from foil container.

title: meringue pie shell
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar; beat until soft peaks form.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar at a time, beating constantly, until stiff peaks form.
Fold in pecans and vanilla.
Spoon into lightly greased pie plate, shaping as for a pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes or until light brown and firm.
Cool.

title: blueberry cream cheese cake
directions: Prepare cream cheese according to directions on box.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Refrigerate at least 20 minutes before serving.

title: gram's vanilla cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 375° until done (approximately 30 minutes).

title: lemon angel pie
directions: Beat 4 egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until it holds a stiff peak.
Turn mixer to low speed and add 1 c. sugar gradually.
Spread in 9 inch buttered pie plate.
Hollow it out in the middle and build up the sides.
Bake at 275 degrees for 1 hour.
Beat 4 egg yolks until thick.
Gradually beat in 1/2 c. sugar, and lemon rind.
Cook over medium heat until thickened. Cool.
Whip whipping cream and spread 1/2 over meringue.
Spread lemon filling over this and top with remaining whipping cream. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pot roast
directions: Preheat frypan at 350°.
Wipe the meat and rub flour over the surface.
Add the fat and brown meat on all sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add water; reduce heat to 225°.
Cover and cook until tender, 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
More water may be added, if needed.
Potatoes, carrots and onions may be added the last 1/2 to 3/4 hour of cooking time.

title: coca-cola pork chops
directions: Mix ketchup and Coke together.
Place pork chops in a baking dish (oblong).
Pour ketchup mixture over pork chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle brown sugar over chops.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until tender.

title: sunny citrus chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Grate zest (outside of peel) of lemon, lime and half the orange into a medium bowl.
Add juice from lemon, lime and orange.
Add olive oil, garlic, salt and cayenne.
Mix well.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: hamburger steaks
directions: Mix all together and shape into size steaks you like.
Fry in butter in skillet until brown.

title: oyster cracker delights
directions: Add the herbs and crackers to 3/4 cup of oil.
Stir periodically until oil is absorbed.
Place in a tight container or jar.
Keeps well.

title: hamburg or meat loaf pie
directions: Mix hamburg same as family favorite meat loaf.
Pat in bottom of pie tins or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until well done.
Drain off fat.
Put favorite vegetable on top of meat.
Fix mashed potatoes and spread on top of vegetable and meat.
Pop back in oven until vegetable and potatoes are hot (10 to 15 minutes).
Sprinkle with cheese and put in oven until melted.
Cut and serve.
(I put beef gravy over top!)
Meal all in one.

title: souper beef
directions: Combine all together in a baking dish.	Bake at 300° for 3 hours or put in crock-pot for 4 to 5 hours or until tender.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; refrigerate for at least one hour.
Mix together broccoli, bacon, onion, sunflower seeds and raisins.
Toss in dressing just before serving.

title: pistachio with crema sauce
directions: Add salt and pepper to ground beef.
Fry until meat juices are absorbed.
Add chopped onion, parsley and 4 tablespoons butter; brown well.
Add tomato sauce and water and simmer until liquid is absorbed, about 15 minutes.

title: my husband's spinach lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling water until all done. Immediately drain in colander.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Set lasagna noodles aside.

title: applesauce loaf
directions: Pick out a baking pan that you can bring directly to the table.
One that's 8-inches square or 10 x 6-inch or 9 to 10-inch round pan or frying pan. Put butter in pan and set in preheated 450° oven.

title: new-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Combine 2/3 cup sugar, flour and dash of salt in heavy saucepan.
In bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, milk and egg yolks.
Whisk into dry ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, whisking constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Set aside.

title: strawberry cream
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine cheese, sugar and salt.
Add 2 tablespoons whipping cream.
Beat until fluffy.
Whip remaining cream; fold into cheese mixture.
Spoon over berries.
Makes 1 3/4 cups sauce.

title: glazed liver-mushroom nibbles
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup beef broth.
Bring remaining broth to boil, pour over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add sherry and chill until mixture reaches consistency of egg white.
Spread bread rounds with 1 tablespoon chicken-liver spread and put on rack over baking sheet.
Top each with mushroom slice and a pimiento strip.
Spoon gelatin carefully over each, making sure surface is completely coated (any gelatin remaining in pan can be scraped up, melted and reused.)
Chill until set.
Makes 2 dozen, about 32 calories each.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Cream well.
Add flour and milk.
Add flavoring.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter crispies
directions: Cream the butter, peanut butter and sugar until smooth.
Add flour alternately with water, mixing well. Shape into 2 rolls. Chill several hours or overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400° in the oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: quick apple pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
In other bowl, mix remaining ingredients and pour over the apple mixture.
No crust needed.
Put in a 9-inch pie plate.

title: whole wheat honey rolls
directions: Mix together water, yeast, salt, honey, margarine and egg. Add 2 cups whole wheat flour and mix well with mixer.
Add 1 cup white flour and mix with mixer.
Add other 2 cups white flour, one at a time and stir with spoon, then knead bread by hand.
Add additional flour if too sticky.
Place in greased pan and allow to rise for several hours or until more than doubled.
Put down in rolls and allow to rise again.
Cook at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: creamed broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and diced onion.
Drain.
Make a white sauce and add cream cheese to melt.
Stir sauce through broccoli.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Mix butter or margarine with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle over top of casserole and return to oven at 275° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: shredded beef sandwiches
directions: Place roast in a baking dish and add remaining ingredients. Bake at 270° until tender. When tender, shred beef with a fork. Serve on rolls or buns. M-mmm!

title: sangria
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Cover and chill 3 to 24 hours. Pour over ice. Serve with a slice of lemon or lime. Serves 8 to 10.

title: skinny ranch dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in an electric blender; process until smooth.
Serve with vegetables.
Yields 3 cups (12 calories, 0% from fat per tablespoon).

title: patty's snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 8 ingredients.
Chill and roll in small balls and roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 8 minutes at 400°.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine biscuit mix, egg, sugar, milk and butter; mix until well blended.
Fold in bananas.
Place batter in greased muffin tins; sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Use more curry if desired for taste.
Good served with licami.

title: barbecued chicken(yield: 8 servings)
directions: Cut chicken into pieces; cut each breast half into halves. Arrange chicken, skin sides up and thickest parts to outside, in oblong baking dish, (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch).

title: tuna loaf
directions: Combine tuna, soup, egg yolks, crumbs, onion, parsley and lemon juice.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is firm.

title: *hot fudge sundae dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan, stir together flour, white sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, the baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa, which has been well blended.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: mardi gras beef broil
directions: Sprinkle meat with 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder.
Broil.
Cook onion, green pepper, herb and remaining garlic powder in oil until tender-crisp.
Drain tomatoes, reserving juice.
Combine juice and cornstarch; add to vegetables.
Cook, stirring, until thickened. Add tomatoes; heat.
Slice meat; top with vegetables.
Serves 4.

title: sunday casserole
directions: Mix together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Can be made the night before and refrigerated to bake in the morning.

title: old fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Bring soup bones and 3 quarts of water to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: cheesy mexicali quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, toss together 1 1/2 cups cheese, squash and flour.
Place in pie shell.
Spoon 1/2 cup salsa over top.
In medium bowl, whisk eggs and evaporated milk. Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: crust for fried pies
directions: Mix dough.
Roll into small circles.
Add 2 tablespoons fruit, sweetened.
Shape into half moons.
Fry to golden brown on both sides in butter flavored shortening.
While hot, pour glaze over both sides.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Dip apples, bananas, oranges or any other fruit to your desire.

title: date-nut cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and let cool a few minutes while you mix other ingredients in a large mixing bowl.

title: macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Slowly beat in sugar until dissolved.
Add vanilla.
Crush corn flakes slightly with hands.
Add flakes and coconut and blend in.
Drop on cookie sheets covered with brown paper from grocery bags.
Bake at 325° until set and slightly browned.
Place wet kitchen towel on counter and slide paper and cookies onto it.
Wait for 1 minute and lift cookies to rack to cool.

title: apple butter
directions: Place in big roaster or kettle and bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours or to desired thickness.
Stir as needed (can use cloves in place of allspice).

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus; reserve liquids.
In heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour and seasonings.
Gradually add 3/4 cup asparagus liquid and milk; cook until thickens and it is smooth.
Stir constantly.
If too thick, you can add a little more milk or asparagus liquid.
Remove from heat.
Butter a medium size casserole.
Layer asparagus spears, egg slices, cheese and almonds, repeating layers until ingredients are used.
Spoon sauce over all and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: six flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in extracts.
Spoon mixture into prepared 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Add glaze if desired. Cool in pan 10 minutes before turning out.

title: sesame chicken breasts with mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Combine flour and paprika.
Dip chicken pieces in lemon juice, then coat with flour.
Sprinkle lightly with sesame seed.
Brown in butter, turning to brown all sides.
Add mushrooms and sherry.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In large saucepan or soup pot, combine chili sauce, ketchup, jelly, brown sugar, lemon juice and onion.
Warm over medium to low heat.
In a large bowl, mix ground beef, salt, tomato sauce and bread crumbs.
Roll mixture into small meatballs.
Add meatballs to sauce gradually and cook over medium heat for 35 to 40 minutes or until done, turning carefully from time to time so the meatballs don't break up.
Refrigerate overnight to let flavors "marry".
Skim off any fat that settles on top.
When ready to serve just rewarm.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Spread mustard on both sides of chicken and sprinkle with pepper.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Melt butter; stir in lemon juice, garlic salt and tarragon.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place chicken on grill over medium coals; baste with sauce and grill 50 to 55 minutes or until done, turning and basting every 10 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add mushroom soup, tomatoes and beans to meat.
Mix together.
Place a layer of tortilla chips in baking dish, then meat mixture, then cheese, then add another layer and top with cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese is melted.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers in oleo until soft.
Add tomato sauce and continue cooking until transparent, stirring often.
Add soups and crawfish.
Simmer 30 minutes with lid on.
Serve over hot rice.

title: low calorie vegetable soup
directions: Cook the frozen mixed vegetables.
Cook the turkey or chicken until done but not brown. Add to cooked vegetables.
Add the onions, chef's season, V-8 juice and rice.
Simmer for about 1 hour. Can freeze and reheat. Gets better each time.

title: sorry cookies
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Put in 14 x 9-inch greased pan and bake in oven at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan.

title: sausage gumbo
directions: Brown sausage in oil, lower heat and add onion.
Cook until onion is soft.
Drain grease and add tomatoes and corn.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cut kielbasa sausage into bite size chunks.
Cook hamburger and drain.
Return to pan; add kielbasa and sausage.
Cook and drain.
In a Dutch oven, add all meats, onion, pepper, pepperoni and mushrooms.
Cook together for 30 minutes.
Add sauce and simmer for 3 hours.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda. Melt the butter, cool slightly, then beat in the eggs.
Add the buttermilk to the egg mixture and blend well.
Pour the liquid into the dry mixture.
Mix sparingly until just barely combined. The batter will be thick. Heat a nonstick griddle.
Drop large spoonfuls of the batter onto the hot griddle.
Fry until brown on the bottom, flip, then brown on the other side.
Makes 8-10 pancakes.
Good with a topping of 2 large apples (peeled, cored and sliced.)
Saute in a little butter and water with cinnamon and brown sugar.

title: black bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans in 10 to 12 cups water.
Boil beans for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 4 hours.
Discard soaking water.
Add broth, 2 cups water, ham hocks and bay leaf. Bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add onion and remaining ingredients, except lemon slices.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove ham hocks.
Discard bone and fat.
Return ham to soup.
Simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf.
Mash some of the beans against the side of kettle with wooden spoon.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: marinated vidalia salad
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Combine water, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over rings and chill at least 3 hours.
Drain. Stir in mayonnaise and celery seed.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: alfredo lite
directions: Prepare pasta according to package direction; drain.
Melt butter or margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic and scallions.
Add flour and stir constantly until paste is formed. Add egg substitute and milk, stirring constantly.
Cook, stirring, until mixture thickens slightly.
Toss mixture with pasta in a large bowl.
Stir in grated cheese, salt and pepper; garnish with parsley and sage, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water, add juice, salt and vinegar.
When gelatin starts to set, beat until foamy, then add cottage cheese, pineapple and salad dressing.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in walnuts and celery.
Chill.

title: ginger-mincemeat bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine dry gingerbread mix, prepared mincemeat and water; beat smooth.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool. Spread with lemon frosting.
Cut into bars.
Decorate with sliced gumdrops.
Makes 24 bars.

title: marinated brussels sprouts(great as an appetizer or with salad.)
directions: Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: lazy day soup
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add to remaining ingredients in crock-pot. Cook on low for 2 hours or more.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix onion, celery, bell pepper, carrots, cucumber, radishes, tomatoes, salt, pepper, garlic powder and bacon.
