Put your Miracle Whip and Ranch dressing, then your cornbread; toss.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, broccoli and onion; toss well.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Brown meat in margarine until done with seasonings.
Add tomato sauce; cook noodles and drain.
Add to meat and let cook slowly for 20 minutes or so.
Cut up green onions, tops and all. Mix these with softened cream cheese and add sour cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute the chopped onion and chopped bell pepper in the margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can put grated cheese on top or put lid on before putting in the oven.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water and cook until tender.
Add milk, butter and parsley.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Choose your own flavor.
Mix all ingredients together; add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet or add more flour and roll them out.
Bake in hot oven at 400° to 500°.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; blend in melted butter.
Press two-thirds of mixture into a lightly buttered 8-inch square cake pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Sprinkle with remaining Maypo mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool; cut into squares.
Serve topped with ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes one 8-inch square.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice apples; divide the apples between two 10-ounce custard cups.
Sprinkle water over apple slices.
Mix flour, sugar, margarine and cinnamon with a fork until crumbly; sprinkle over apples.
Bake until the top is light golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: elbow macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook elbows and drain.
Place in buttered casserole.
Melt butter in double boiler.
Add flour, salt and pepper and blend. Add milk slowly until sauce thickens.
Cut cheese into cubes; add to sauce.
Stir constantly until cheese has melted.
Pour cheese sauce over elbows and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well in a large pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until dough clings together in a ball.
Cool and knead.
Store in an airtight container.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer in greased 9 x 13-inch pan:
white bread, sausage and cheese.
Blend together and pour over the layers: milk, salt, eggs, mustard and pepper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: easy beef dinner
directions: Secure 1 large elephant.
Kill, clean and cut into small cubes. This will take about 2 months.
Put in a large kettle and simmer over kerosene heat at 465° for 14 weeks.
Make gravy to cover. This will feed 3,685 people.
If more meat is needed, add 2 rabbits.
But use only if necessary as few people care for hare in their stew!

title: chicken breast with long grain and wild rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of a large shallow baking dish.
Pour chicken over rice.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dot with butter. Add mushrooms. Sprinkle onion soup mix over all.
Dilute mushroom soup with a little water and spoon over each breast.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Then cook, covered, for 1/2 hour longer.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients into bowl.
Add egg, milk and shortening. Beat with eggbeater until smooth.
Pour into greased 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: onion casserole
directions: Melt the oleo and saute the onions until clear.
Layer the onions with the crackers. Sprinkle cheese on each layer.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Roll out crescent rolls from package, pressing out all perforations.
Spread lightly with mustard.
Spread sausage over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Slice into rounds.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons in cup of boiled water.
Placed in decorative jar makes nice gift.
Some folks say it even cures their cold!

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Fondue Dippers:

Apple, pear, peach, banana and cherries brushed with lemon juice to prevent browning; strawberries, pineapple chunks and mandarin oranges (fruit should be well drained); Ladyfingers, pieces of pound or angel food cake, nuts or marshmallows.

title: chicken and macaroni with mushrooms
directions: Spray a slow cooker container with butter flavored cooking spray. In the cooker, combine the chicken soup and sour cream. Stir in chicken, mushrooms and onion. Add uncooked macaroni. Mix well. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Gently stir again just before serving.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water.
Cool.
Add shrimp and crushed pineapple.
Toss with mayonnaise.
(Can add more mayonnaise if not enough for you.)

title: sloppy joes("kid's favorite")
directions: Cook meat and onion together, breaking it up into pieces. Drain off fat. Add rest of ingredients and simmer over low heat, covered, approximately 30 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: sixty minute rolls
directions: Combine milk, water and butter in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are warm.
Pour into bowl and add sugar, salt, yeast and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 1/2 cup flour and beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and place on 98° pan of water to rise for 15 minutes.
Turn dough onto floured board.
Divide in half and shape as desired.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and oil.
Add sifted dry ingredients and carrots.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add nuts and blend well.
Pour into oiled loaf pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cover cake with foil during first 20 minutes of baking to prevent cracking.

title: my favorite sugar cookies
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients by hand or mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make into balls the size of a walnut.
Dip glass into sugar and press cookie flat.
May use red or green sugar to decorate if you make them for Christmas.
Bake at 350° to light brown.
They melt in your mouth.

title: eggs-in-sausage
directions: Make sausage into equal patties.
Take each patty and completely wrap 1 boiled egg.
Do all 6 patties in this manner. Roll each one in flour and fry on all sides until browned all over. Really tasty and different.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Make the cornbread.
Crumble into small pieces and spread in a 9 x 13 dish.
Pour the pinto beans over the cornbread.
Spread the bell pepper over the pinto beans.
Spread the onion over the pepper.
Spread the tomatoes over the onion.
Mix the Ranch dressing and pickle juice together and pour over salad.
Sprinkle bacon bits or real crumbled bacon on top.
Serve at room temperature or cold.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Add flavorings; mix well.
Fold in pecans and chocolate chips.
Drop by heaping teaspoon onto an aluminum foil lined cookie sheet.
Place in a 350° oven.
Turn oven off.
Let stand for 8 to 10 hours or overnight (do not open oven).
Store in airtight container.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread in large baking pan (9 x 13). Mix all ingredients with cornbread. Refrigerate.

title: citrus tea
directions: In a teapot, pour boiling water over tea bags; cover and brew 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags; stir in sugar and cool.
In a large pitcher combine tea with remaining ingredients; chill.
Serve with ice chunks or crushed ice.

title: bride's quick and easy coffee cake
directions: Melt stick of butter and mix half of the butter with sugar. Add remaining ingredients and pour into buttered pan.
Pour remaining butter over batter, then sprinkle heavily with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well as listed.
Cool or chill if possible, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook as cookies don't brown much.
Let cookies sit on cookie sheet for at least 5 minutes before placing on cooling rack.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In a quart saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and water.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat; cook until candy thermometer reaches 280° or candy forms a ball when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add salt.
Pour over popcorn; stir to coat well.
Shape into balls with buttered hands.
Makes 12 popcorn balls.

title: chicken louise
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with 1/2-inch of one vegetable (celery, broccoli or asparagus).
Cut chicken in strips. Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Roll chicken in flour mixture, then brown chicken in butter.
Lay chicken on top of vegetable.
Mix cheese, soup and half and half and pour over chicken.
Top with slivered almonds and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all except potato chips.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 10 or more.

title: mom's lime congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and cream cheese with water.
After it thickens, add pineapple and nuts; fold in Cool Whip.
Chill and keep in refrigerator.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Lightly saute onion, bell pepper and pimento pepper in 1 cup of margarine over medium heat.
Then add Cheez Whiz, broccoli, Minute rice and mushroom soup.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deep dish mexican pie
directions: Thaw deep dish pie shell and bake 10 minutes. Mix beans and picante sauce, spread 1/2 mixture on bottom of pie shell.
Brown meat and add seasoning as directed on package, spread 1/2 mixture on top of bean mixture along with one cup of cheese.
Add a layer of Tostitos, then repeat first two layers.
Make circle on edge of top of pie with chopped green chiles.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with chopped tomato.
Freezes well.

title: seasoned roast beef
directions: Use toothpicks to hold bacon slices onto roast.
Slice 2 to 3 holes in meat and put in elephant garlic, then sprinkle with pepper.
Put teriyaki sauce, liquid smoke and onion (cut into quarters) into a roasting bag with the beef and cook until done by meat thermometer.

title: tarts
directions: Sift flour into a large bowl.
Make a hole in the center.
Dip up a small portion of the flour in the sifter. Add the soda, baking powder and salt. Sift together into the hole made in the flour.
Pour in the peanut oil and buttermilk; mix to a dough stiff enough to roll out into small round pieces.
Place enough fruit on the circle to fill one side. Turn the other side over. Press down with a fork.
Fry in hot oil.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crush wafers fine with a rolling pin.
Add butter, lemon juice and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix well.
Press firmly on bottom and about half way up sides of a 9-inch spring-form cake pan.
Beat cheese until softened.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, the flour and salt.
Blend.
Beat in milk and vanilla. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff, but not dry.
Fold carefully and thoroughly into first mixture.
Pour into crumb-lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until firm.
Cool.
Remove sides of pan.

title: raisin carrot muffins(lo-cal, low-fat)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine last 7 ingredients.
Make a well in flour mixture.
Add wet ingredients. Stir just enough to mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 22 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.

title: pralines
directions: Mix sugar, soda, milk and syrup.
Pour into a 2-quart boiler and let reach a soft ball or 238°.
Add butter and vanilla, then beat until it is thick enough to drop from a teaspoon.

title: stir-fry vegetables with baked tofu
directions: Slice tofu 1/4 to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut broccoli florets about 3/4-inch long.
Peel carrot and broccoli; stalk should be sliced diagonally.
Cut pepper into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: creamy chilled cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: zucchini hamburger dish
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Add
onions and brown.
Add sliced zucchini (cut in bite sizes).
Cover and steam until zucchini is hot through but crisp.
Add sliced tomatoes, steam until tender. Add diced or cut up cheese.
Cover until melted.
Season to taste. Serves 4.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Cook over low to medium heat until thickened.
Add 3/4 c shredded coconut and 1 c chopped pecans.
Beat until cooled. Spread over cooled chocolate cake.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone. Cut in chunks.
Mix chicken, soup, sour cream and mushrooms together and put in casserole.
Crumble crackers with melted butter and sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme and softened cream cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Serve with strawberries or desired fruit.

title: clay molds
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Gradually add water.
Make desired shapes. Bake at 225° for about 30 minutes. Let cool. Use tempera paints.

title: glenn's melanzane con due formaggi(eggplant with two cheeses)
directions: Liberally salt both sides of eggplant slices and let drain for 15 minutes.
Wash salt off and pat dry.
Mix flour and garlic salt and use to coat eggplant slices.

title: graham cracker cream pie
directions: Mix graham crackers, flour, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and melted butter for pie crust.
Take half of mixture and pack into pie pan.
Combine egg yolks, milk, 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and vanilla and cook until this mixture thickens.
Pour into the pie pan.
Whip together the egg whites and 3 Tbsp. sugar.
Whip until it forms a thick meringue and spread on top of custard.
Sprinkle remaining cracker crumb mixture over top of meringue.
Bake in moderate oven, 325°, until meringue is brown.
Serves 6.

title: wine biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder in a bowl.
Make a well in the center; add oil and wine.
Mix together thoroughly.
Pinch off pieces of dough about 1-inch in diameter.
Roll pieces between palms into cigarette-shaped cylinders, then bring ends together and pinch to form circles.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Brush tops with beaten egg yolk.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes, until bottoms look dry.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: polish sausage with baked beans
directions: Mix pork and beans, onion, brown sugar and tomato sauce in a large bowl.
Pour mixture in baking dish.
Top with sausage and cover with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peter pan choco surprises
directions: Cream peanut butter, margarine and sugar.
Beat eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add gradually until well blended.
Chill dough at least 30 minutes.

title: eula's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice vegetables very thin.
Put in container.
Add salt; stir and cover with ice and let set 3 hours.
Drain well and make syrup with remaining ingredients.
Heat to boil.
Put in jar and seal.

title: sweet onion relish
directions: Mix vinegar, oil and sugar to a boil until sugar is dissolved over low heat.
Cool.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour dressing over.
Chill and serve.

title: southwestern stew
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: plum jelly
directions: Boil plums and water together until fruit is soft.
Press through colander.
Drip through jelly bag.
Bring juice to boil. Add sugar to juice (3/4 cup sugar to 1 cup juice).
Stir until dissolved.
Boil until jelly flakes from spoon.
Skim and pour into hot sterilized glasses.
Seal with hot lids and rings.

title: pecan sweets
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add the pecans.
Stir until all pecans are coated.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Pour over pecans and mix well.
Put on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam spray.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 20 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix everything with mixer except crushed Oreos. Pour into dish and top with crushed Oreos and gummy worms.
Chill.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars and pudding mix in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in oats and raisins. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate dessert waffles
directions: Combine cocoa, flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the milk. Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gently fold into the batter.
Preheat waffle maker and bake waffles according to manufacturer's directions.
Serve waffles warm or room temperature with ice cream, warmed chocolate sauce and fresh raspberries.
Yield:
6-8 servings.

title: miniature tea tarts
directions: Mix well; mold well in miniature muffin tins.

title: peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Mix peanut butter and butter together.
Stir in confectioners sugar.
Form small eggs and refrigerate.
Slowly melt milk chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Dip eggs in melted chocolate; cool and decorate.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Parboil the broccoli.
Drain.
Put in a buttered 9 x 9-inch dish.
Add the cubed chicken.
Mix together the soup, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Spread over chicken.
Top with the cheese. Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine oats, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon, and dash salt.
Cut in butter till mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Set aside.
Peel, core and slice apples to make 5 - 6 cups.
Place fruit in a 10 by 6 by 2 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over all.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Bring milk to a boil; set aside to cool to room temperature. Add
Crisco.
Mix yeast and 1/4 cup of hot water; pour into
milk. When
it
is
at
room temperature, add sugar and flour (one
cup at a time).
Knead for 10 minutes.
Set aside to raise for 2 to 3 hours.

title: cream cheese butter pecan frosting
directions: Stir together chopped pecans and 1/2 c butter, spread pecans in an even layer in a 13 x 9 inch pan. Bake in 350 degree oven for 15 minutes or until pecans are toasted.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Beat cream cheese and butter (1/2 c) at medium speed until creamy.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Spread between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: cinnamon pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs with wire whisk to blend well.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until thoroughly blended and smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 15 minutes at 425°, then bake 35 minutes at 350° until filling is set in center and slightly puffed.

title: butter bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: eileen's tomato noodle soup
directions: Place chuck in large soup pan with vegetables and seasonings. Cover with water; bring to boil, then reduce heat and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is very tender.
Add water occasionally if necessary.
Remove meat and shred.
Place meat back into broth, then add tomato juice and cook on low heat at least another hour. Prepare noodles per package.
Drain and add to soup about 1/2 hour before serving.
Flavor is best 2nd day.
May add more noodles if broth is flavorful.

title: tortilla omelet
directions: Mix together peas, onion, tomatoes, ham and leave overnight to blend flavors.
Scramble eggs and put in a pan.
Cook like an omelet with mixture in center.

title: bernice's cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into a stick about as thick as a half dollar.
Chill and slice into really thin slices.
Leave plenty of room on the baking sheet for them to spread.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: chewy chocolate meltaway cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Beat well. Add flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Mix well.
Drop onto ungreased baking sheet by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes. Top with mint and bake for 2 minutes more.
Spread mint over top of cookies.
Great at Christmas time.

title: beef oriental casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger, onions and celery. Add the rice. Stir well and put in casserole dish. Add the remaining ingredients. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: white christmas pizza
directions: Spread crust with butter; toast under broiler.
Set aside. Combine next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Spread over crust.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Top with remaining ingredients.

title: crunch chicken delight
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
In a
bowl,
make a batter by
mixing
together
the flour, egg,
ice
water	and garlic. In	a
shallow
dish, place the
bread
crumbs.
Dip chicken first in batter, turning to coat evenly,	then
in the bread crumbs, rolling
to
coat.	In
a large frying pan, fill with oil 1/2-inch, so chicken fits with ease.
Drain chicken.

title: thanksgiving pot pie
directions: Soak cranberries in sherry.
Set aside.
Boil water; add carrots and cook until tender, about 2 minutes.
Add leeks and cook about 1 1/2 minutes.
Drain.
Cook mushrooms in 1 tablespoon oil about 5 minutes.
Mix together turkey, drained cranberries (reserve sherry) and all vegetables.
Add tarragon, parsley and orange zest. Heat broth and sherry.
Melt butter over medium low heat; add flour and cook, stirring, until it browns lightly, about 3 minutes. Slowly whisk in hot broth and whisk over medium-high heat until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fold white sauce into vegetables and meat and remove to a round 2 to 3-quart casserole dish.

title: deluxe oyster crackers
directions: Mix dressing, oil, dill weed and garlic powder.
Pour over crackers in bowl and keep stirring until all liquid is absorbed. Eat and enjoy.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add rest and mix until smooth.
Pour into 2 medium greased loaf pans or 3 small greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate covered coconut candy
directions: Dip
balls
in	melted	chocolate with spoon.
Place on waxed paper to cool.
This candy is very much like Mounds.

title: pot roast
directions: In a large pan or slo-cooker, put meat and cover with water. Add onion.
Cook 3 to 4 hours if on stove.
If in slo-cooker, cook on high.
When meat is almost done, add cut-up celery, carrots and potatoes and cook until the vegetables are done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot pepper jelly(this jelly is not hot.)
directions: Mix peppers, (some juice, about 1/3 cup), vinegar and sugar. Add green food coloring.
Bring to a rolling boil (one that can't be stirred down), on high heat.
Remove from heat and cool 5 Immediately add Certo and stir.
Immediately pour into jars. Makes 7 (8 ounce) jars.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak buttermilk and oats for 1 hour.
Cream together oil, brown sugar, salt and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes in 400° oven.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: apple cinnamon french toast
directions: The day before, prepare apples and French bread by melting butter in skillet and cooking apples until tender. Add brown sugar, corn syrup and cinnamon. Cook until sugar dissolves. Pour apple mixture into a 9 x 13 inch pan and spread evenly. Arrange bread slices on top. In a bowl, beat eggs, milk and vanilla, and pour over bread slices. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: washday casserole
directions: Pour hamburger and onions into casserole.
Add potatoes, celery and cooked spaghetti.
Pour soup over top.
Fry bacon and lay on top.
Pour tomato juice over this.
Add Cheddar cheese. Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: abby's cheesecake
directions: Melt butter and add to graham cracker crumbs and sugar. Line the bottom of spring-form pan; pack firmly.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Chop up and combine chicken, cabbage, almonds, sesame seed, onion and Top Ramen noodles into large bowl.
In small bowl, combine oil, seasonings and any seasoning package from noodles. Mix and pour over cabbage mixture.
Toss and chill.
Tastes best when served the next day.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: cauliflower cheese pudding
directions: Rinse cauliflower and cut into flowerets.
Place in a microsafe shallow dish (in single layer just to fit).
Microwave on High power for 4 minutes, covered tightly.
In a bowl, combine the half and half, eggs, salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour mixture over the steamed cauliflower.
Add sliced red pepper.
Sprinkle with paprika and a little extra cheese.
Microwave on High power, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Stir slightly to blend outer cooked custard with inner custard.
Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes longer on High power.
Cover tightly.
Microwave on High power for 3 to 4 minutes, until custard is set.
Remove.
Uncover carefully and serve.

title: slush
directions: Make tea with the 2 cups of boiling water and tea bags.
Make the tea strong.
Mix all ingredients except 7-Up.
Freeze.
Will be a slush.
Serve 2 or 3 tablespoons of frozen slush with a glass of 7-Up.
You can garnish with cherry and slice of orange.
Enjoy.

title: toasted coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook until thick over medium heat, about 12 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add pecans and coconut; beat until cool and thick enough to spread.

title: broccoli cheese chicken rice bake
directions: Prepare rice mix according to package directions.
In a 12x8 inch baking dish arrange rice mix, lengthwise across center of dish.
Arrange chicken over rice, overlapping if necessary. Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes until chicken is fork tender.

title: turkey-bean chili
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave at High 5 to 6 minutes, or until meat is no longer pink, stirring once.
Drain well.
Add tomato sauce, beans, salt, pepper, chili powder and cumin.
Cover; microwave at High 10 to 12 minutes, stirring after 6 minutes.
If desired, garnish with sour cream and green onions.
Yields 5 cups.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In a large bowl, put croutons and margarine; toss gently.
Add hot water and sauerkraut.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread chicken on top of broccoli.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Combine breadcrumbs, cheese, oregano, salt and pepper on waxed paper; set aside. Wipe veal with damp paper towels.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Pound very thin, using mallet or edge of plate.
Dip veal into beaten eggs, then into crumb mixture, coating well on both sides.
Slowly heat oil in large skillet. Saute cutlets, a few at a time, until golden brown, about three minutes on each side.
Remove to heated platter; keep warm.
Drain fat from skillet.
Stir in wine and bring to boiling, stirring to dissolve browned bits in pan; pour over veal.

title: southern spiced pecans
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add cumin and cayenne pepper. Cook and stir for one minute.
Remove from heat; stir in pecans, sugar and salt until well coated.
Spread in single layer in a greased baking dish (13 x 10).
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Store in airtight container.

title: fruit pies
directions: Mix cornstarch and pineapple. Cook until thick.
Mix all other ingredients except bananas.
Let cook about a minute.
Add bananas.
Stir together.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with Cool Whip.
Let chill at least 4 hours before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients except parsley.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sweet and sour pickled beets
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour off some liquid from beets.
Mix vinegar mixture and beets.
Fill jars with beet mixture.
Seal jar with lid and cover.
Do not use at least for one week.
Jars should be sterilized.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a heavy pan and bring very slowly to boil, stirring until all sugar is melted.
Cover and boil without stirring for 3 minutes so all sugar crystals are dissolved.
Uncover and boil on medium heat to 240°.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes.
Do not stir.

title: volcano salad
directions: Prepare chicken by boiling it and debone and dice.
Cool chicken.
Thicken broth with cornstarch.
Prepare rest of ingredients into individual bowls.
Prepare the rice.
It takes about 5 minutes.
Place on plate in following order:
rice, chicken, gravy, pineapple, onion, celery, sunflower kernels, coconut, chow mein noodles and gravy again.

title: old-fashion chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil one hen until tender.
Season with chopped onion and salt and pepper.
Allow to cool and debone chicken, reserving broth. Mix flour, eggs, salt, oleo and milk together.
Knead until stiff. Roll out to thickness of pie crust.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch strips. Bring broth to a rolling boil and drop in dumplings one at a time. Cook about 15 minutes.
Add chicken.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil the chicken in water until fully cooked.
Remove chicken from pot, saving chicken stock.
In separate pan, melt stick of butter.
Add bell pepper, onion and celery.
Cook vegetables until tender.
While vegetables are cooking, bone the chicken.
When vegetables are tender, add soups and chicken.
Stir until mixed. Add chili powder and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add pimento and simmer together for 15 minutes.
In separate pan, cook spaghetti.
When spaghetti and sauce are finished, mix together and serve.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put layer of coconut, layer of chocolate chips, sprinkle on a few pecans, layer of coconut, layer of chocolate chips and layer of pecans.
Pour both cans of condensed milk over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a saucepan, mix together butter and flour over low heat for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and bouillon, whipping until mixed.
Mix in Velveeta and broccoli and stir occasionally until thick and creamy, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cafe au lait
directions: Scald cream in a small saucepot over medium-high heat.
Do not boil.
Add the hot Cajun Coffee.
Blend well into the cream and sweeten with sugar.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Heat 1 cup of milk and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Mix cornstarch, 1/2 cup milk and egg yolks.
Add to hot mixture slowly. (Cook in double boiler until thick.)
Stir and add butter 10 minutes longer.
Cool.
Make meringue and top pie with it.
Brown and cool crust before pouring in filling.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, syrup and salt in 2-quart microwave bowl.
Bring to boil in microwave and let boil for 2 minutes.
Add soda and stir.
Pour mixture over popcorn that has been place in paper grocery sack; shake well.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes. Take out and shake.
Repeat 2 more times and cool.

title: whipping cream corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Grease muffin pan with Pam. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan, cook at 350° for 12 minutes. Combine softened cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Add remaining milk and pudding.
Mix and let stand 1 minute.
Spread over cake. Top with crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.

title: baked baby carrots supreme
directions: Scrape washed baby carrots.
Put in heavy baking dish with 1/4 inch water in bottom.
Mix oleo and garlic.
Add to baking dish. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Add flour into mixing bowl.
Add salt, baking powder, shortening, milk and eggs.
Mix with a spoon until thoroughly mixed.
Knead mixture with floured hands on floured wax paper. Divide into 3 balls.
Roll each ball out thin and cut into strips. Cook hen tender; cover hen with water in a big pot.
Season with salt, pepper, celery and onion.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Cook rice or herb-flavored rice mix according to package directions.
Meanwhile rinse chicken; pat dry.
Sprinkle both sides of chicken with lemon pepper and onion powder.
In a skillet cook chicken in margarine or butter over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until no longer pink, turning once.
Transfer to a platter.
Keep warm.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash the broccoli and cauliflower and cut the ends into bite-size pieces (do not use stems).
Put into a large bowl; add 1 bottle of bacon bits.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in large baking dish.
Melt 1 stick butter and mix with 1 roll Ritz crackers, crushed.
Sprinkle on top of vegetables.
Cook at 300° for about 30 minutes until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with crackers, including up the sides of pan.
Mix pudding with milk; beat one or two minutes.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Layer pudding mix and more crackers, ending with crackers.
Put opened can of icing in microwave for 1 minute on high heat.
Pour icing on top of crackers and spread to edges. Refrigerate for 8 hours.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Puree enough strawberries to equal 3/4 cup. Reserve rest.
In saucepan, mix gelatine with 1/4 cup sugar. Blend in egg yolks beaten with milk.

Let stand 1 minute. Stir over low heat until gelatine dissolves, about 5 minutes. With wire whip, blend in pureed strawberries, yogurt, lemon juice and food coloring. Chill. Stir occasionally until mix mounds slightly.
In a bowl, beat whites until stiff, gradually adding remaining sugar. Fold into gelatine mixture.
Put in crust and chill until firm.
Garnish with remaining strawberries.

title: shoo-fly pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix together flour, 1/3 teaspoon soda and oleo to make crumbs. Pour 1/2 hot liquid into pie shells (unbaked), then sprinkle 1/2 crumbs, then rest of liquid and remaining crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Mix in bowl the butter for 30 seconds.
Add peanut butter and sugars; beat.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add chocolate chips; stir.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Make cake mix according to the package directions.
Fill paper bake cups in muffin pan 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese with the sugar.
Beat in egg and salt. Stir in the chocolate pieces.
Drop one rounded teaspoonful cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as per cake mix directions.
Makes about 30.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and 10x sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and pecans. Blend well.
Roll mixture into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 30 minutes.
While warm, roll in 10x sugar.
Cool and roll again in sugar mixture.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add buttermilk.
Add cocoa and sugar together.
Sift flour 3 times.
Add jam to flour; mix well and then put other ingredients in.
Makes two 9-inch layers. Bake at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: darnisha's irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 in. apart onto ungreased cookie baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross patterns with fork.
Bake for 7-8 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove cookies to foil to cool completely.

title: grilled marinated chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow pan.
Combine salad dressing mix and oil.
Pour over chicken breasts; toss to coat well.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Place chicken on greased grill over glowing coals.
Grill, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender, brushing frequently with marinade.
Remove from grill. Place vegetables on grill; turn frequently until just crisp, about 3 minutes.
Place romaine lettuce on serving platter.
Arrange chicken breasts on lettuce with broccoli and peppers.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and pepper if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cold pan popovers
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased muffin tins, about 2/3 full.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.
Do not preheat the oven.
Put all your ingredients in a bowl and use a wooden spoon to mix.
Beat the eggs a little before you put in flour. These popovers are easy to make and very good, they are filled with lots of air bubbles.

title: old virginia spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2-quart baking dish; set aside. Pour water over corn meal in bowl; stir until slightly cool.
Beat egg yolks with electric mixer until lemon colored.
Stir egg yolks and butter into corn meal; blend well.
Stir in buttermilk and sugar.
Beat egg whites in separate bowl until soft peaks form. Fold egg whites into corn meal mixture until blended.
Pour into prepared baking dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve hot with butter.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: Cream
margarine
and
sugar.
Add
flavorings and egg; mix well.
Mix	in flour and salt to form a soft dough.
Shape cookies with a cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at
400° for 6 to 9 minutes.
Cool cookies.	Melt equal parts sweet chocolate
and semi-sweet chocolate in microwave.
Coat cookies by dipping in chocolate.
Dry on waxed paper.
(Hint: If chocolate is too thick, thin with melted vegetable shortening.)

title: easy pie
directions: Mix in large bowl and pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: carolyn's chicken
directions: Line casserole with bacon strips; add rice.
Salt and pepper chicken and place over rice.
Mix soup with water.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle lightly with oregano.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Combine water, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, salt, margarine, sugar and raisins in saucepan; boil for 3 minutes.
When cool, add flour, baking powder and soda.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at between 325° and 350°.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Take corn meal.
Mix with stock from turkey.
Bake in pan, not too brown, but just cooked through.
Crumble this in a large bowl and add toasted white bread, cold biscuits or cold grits to make amount you want.
Add boiled eggs, onion, pepper, salt and a little sage or poultry seasoning if you like.
Pour turkey stock over mixture to make as soft as you like.
Bake in a flat Pyrex dish or pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares and place around the turkey.

title: wilma's italian salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Rinse well in cold water.
Mix everything together.
Pour the juice from the artichoke hearts in your salad (1 jar only), everything else drain first.
When adding Italian dressing, add to your taste.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar and cream.
Cook until done.
Add butter, soda and vanilla.
Mix.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Melt Crisco in cast-iron skillet.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and mix with hands, adding more flour, if necessary.
Divide dough into 9 equal balls. Flatten each ball.
Lay in skillet in melted Crisco and turn to coat both sides of biscuit with Crisco.

title: quiche zucchini
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients with beaten eggs. Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until golden brown. Cut in pieces.
Easy and delicious.
Bon appetit!

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Pour scalded milk into a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Let stand until lukewarm. Blend in eggs.
Sprinkle yeast in lukewarm water and stir yeast until dissolved. Add to milk mixture. Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough. Cover and set in warm place until double in size.
Turn out on floured board and knead dough until smooth and not sticky.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Store in refrigerator until needed.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Prepare jello.	When
thickened fold in crushed pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Place
in
large
cake pan and let set. Mix together flour and sugar in saucepan; add beaten eggs and pineapple juice
and Tang.	Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add cream
cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted. When cooled, place
on
jello.
Chill
overnight.
Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, layer the ingredients.
Cut lettuce to desired size.
Add small box of frozen peas.
Add celery.
Spread cup of mayonnaise evenly over top.
Add grated cheese and crumble bacon over the top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: guacamole dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients except bacon; mix well.
Cover and chill 30 minutes or until served.
Before serving, stir in bacon or use as garnish.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: 5 layer dinner
directions: Pat ground beef into bottom of pan.
Place onions on meat. Add cheese slices.
Place potatoes on top.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: simple salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Cover. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sugar.
By hand, add the Cool Whip. Put on top of crust and put in refrigerator.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes; chunk into pieces.
Add chopped onion.
Cover potatoes completely with water; add salt and cook until tender. Use potato masher and mash potatoes until in small pieces.
Do not drain off liquid.
Add milk, Cheez Whiz, seasoning salt and parsley flakes.
Add bacon.
Heat soup until cheese is melted. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with spices and mix with first 5.
Makes 5 to 7 servings.

title: beefy mushroom noodles
directions: Mix all together, season to taste with salt, pepper, garlic, parsley and heat through. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: 4 cheese baked macaroni
directions: Mix bread crumbs, parsley and Parmesan cheese together; set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni approximately 9 minutes or until tender.
Drain and rinse under cold water.
Heat 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Add onion.
Saute for 3 minutes.
Add flour.
Cook over low heat for 1 minute.
Gradually add milk.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Stir in other cheeses, reserving 1 cup Fontina.
Simmer until cheese melts. Season with cayenne pepper, salt and pepper.
Stir mixture into macaroni.
Pour mixture into greased casserole.
Top with remaining cheese, then bread crumb mixture.
Drizzle remaining butter on top.
Bake until golden brown 40 minutes uncovered.

title: broccoli - lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans and broccoli separately; then mix together. Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sour cream, soups and water chestnuts.
Pour over vegetables.
Brown Rice Krispies in butter.
Pour Rice Krispies over top and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into loaf.
Put into 2-quart loaf pan.
Spoon barbecue sauce over meat.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp-crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with 1/2 cup buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in rectangular glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or microwave for 15 to 20 minutes on roast.

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: Brown roast over medium heat.
Add onion soup mix blended with water.
Simmer, covered, turning occasionally 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
If desired, thicken gravy.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and shape into balls. Chill 30 minutes. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fancy franks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Slice each hot dog in half lengthwise. In a small bowl, crumble onions with your fingers.
Reserve 2 tablespoons for topping.
Combine potatoes, butter, onions, salt and pepper in a 9 x 13-inch dish and blend well.
Combine soup and milk in a small bowl.
Pour 3/4 of the soup mixture over the potato mixture and blend.
Arrange hot dogs, cut side down, on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle reserved 2 tablespoons onions on top and pour remaining soup mixture over onions.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes.

title: christmas bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together, then add the eggs (well beaten), then the yeast dissolved in warm water, then the potato and mix the whole with the milk which has been warmed and the vanilla.
When it is well mixed, add the melted butter and mix well.
Finally add the flour mixture and nuts.
(If you reserve part of the flour to stir into this fruit and nut mixture, it will more easily mix evenly into the dough.)
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Divide into 2 or 3 bread pans (depending on size of pans).
Let rise again and bake in a moderate oven (around 325° to 350°) for about 45 minutes.
Cool in the pans on racks for about 5 minutes.
Remove from pans and set loaves on racks to cool thoroughly before storing.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Mix chopped cabbage and onion in a large bowl.
Take dry Ramen noodles and crush into small pieces.
Use seasoning packet in saucepan with oil and vinegar.
Toss cabbage mixture with dressing (oil, vinegar and seasoning packet).
Add dry, crushed noodles, sesame seed and slivered almonds just before serving and toss well.
Eat while noodles are still crunchy for best flavor.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Preheat broiler.
Broil steak 6 inches from heat until rare, about 5 minutes on each side.
Cut diagonally into thin, 2-inch strips, set aside.
In a large frying pan, bring broth to a boil. Add onion and mushrooms.
Simmer, covered, about 5 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Remove vegetables with a slotted spoon; set aside.
Simmer broth until reduced to 1/2 cup; remove from heat. Combine water, flour and cornstarch; mix well.
Stir into broth with a wire whisk.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Combine yogurt, paprika, salt, garlic powder and mustard.
Add to chicken broth, stirring until smooth.
Mix in reserved beef, onion and mushrooms.
Warm over very low heat, stirring constantly until hot, about 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles, if desired.

title: chicken cacciatore with vermicelli
directions: Shake chicken halves in a clean paper bag filled with seasoned flour.
In a large frying pan, brown chicken on both sides in a generous amount of heated olive oil.
Arrange chicken in a single layer in a large baking pan; pour Tomato Sauce over chicken.
Bake uncovered in a slow oven (325°) for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
(After 45 minutes baking, spoon half the sauce out of pan with chicken and combine it with cooked hot vermicelli.
Keep warm in oven.)
At serving time, arrange chicken on one serving platter, vermicelli on another.
Sprinkle vermicelli liberally with Parmesan.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Form dough into
walnut sized balls and press out with fork.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: deer lovers delight
directions: Marinate roast overnight in buttermilk, salt, pepper and garlic powder at room temperature.
Drain roast until marinate ceases dripping.
Place in roasting pan.
Roast for 2 hours at 350°, rotate, baste with marinate leftover after draining.
Cook for another 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.
Take roast out of pan and add 2 tablespoons of flour mixed with 2/3 cup water, shake well and add to drippings in the pan.
Bring to a boil and make a gravy to the consistency at which you like.
This is one of the best Downing recipes for a good wild game meal.
Enjoy!

title: quick corn chowder
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle each serving with green onions and bacon bits.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham and almond haystacks
directions: Combine the cheese, Miracle Whip, green onion, pickle relish and ham together.
Shape into 1 large or 2 smaller haystack mounds.
Combine the Miracle Whip and cream cheese. Frost the mounds with it.
Cover with the slivered almonds.

title: stir-fried mandarin pineapple chicken
directions: Heat oil in wok or skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Continue stir-frying 3 to 4 minutes.
Fold in pineapple and heat thoroughly.
Serve hot.
(I use Hormel canned chicken, drained.)

title: curry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill at least 3 hours. Serve with fresh vegetables.
Makes 1 cup.

title: catfish mulldown
directions: Fry catfish and remove from bones.
Layer catfish, onions, potatoes, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Top with catsup and hot sauce. Simmer on low heat until potatoes and onions are done, approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and peppers slowly in oil until soft.
Add hamburger and cook until brown.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Bake in covered casserole at 375° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar and shortening.
Dissolve soda in sour milk and add flour, baking powder and oatmeal along with the eggs.
Add corn flakes and peanuts.
Bake at 375°.

title: cake and puddin
directions: In an oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2, mix sugar and cocoa; stir in water.
Snip marshmallows in fourths and scatter over mixture. Prepare cake mix according to directions and spoon over mixture. Sprinkle nuts on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350°.
This will have a rich pudding on bottom.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake (5 to 6 weeks).
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: english sugar cookies
directions: Beat oleo, sugar, milk and egg.
Add vanilla and all dry ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Grease pan.
Roll and cut out. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions. In separate pan, cook zucchini. Drain. In large baking dish, mix hamburger, zucchini and drained tomatoes. Top with 2 cups of grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Spread butter liberally on one side of four slices of bread and place on grill, butter side down.
Top with pastrami, sauerkraut and Swiss cheese.
While sandwiches brown, spread butter on remaining slices of bread.
Those who like very moist sandwiches may like mayonnaise spread on the inside of the bread.
Turn over and brown on remaining side.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles per directions; cool.
Mix all ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and the 2 sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs. Mix soda, salt and 1/4 cup flour.
Beat in.
Add rest of flour and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons (scant) on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: creole snack mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a roasting pan.
Drizzle half of the margarine over cereal mixture.
Sprinkle with half of the seasonings.
Stir.
Repeat with remaining margarine and seasonings.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes. Yields 12 cups.

title: manly texas quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 425° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven. Prick lightly with fork and let cool.

title: kugel(noodle pudding)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put eggs, sugar, salt and cinnamon in mixing bowl and mix well.
Add cooked noodles, cottage cheese, sour cream, grated apple and vanilla.
Mix well.
Generously grease sides and bottom of 2-quart casserole with butter or margarine.
Pour in noodle mixture and smooth top.
Bake for one hour or until top is nicely browned.
Remove from oven and cool for about 20 minutes.
To serve Kugel, cut into squares and serve as a side dish with meat or chicken.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell and cool.
Wash and remove stems from strawberries.
Arrange strawberries in pie shell.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over medium heat until mixture turns clear and thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Put in refrigerator until firm.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme and milk, mixing with electric mixer until well blended.
Add peanut butter, beating until light and fluffy.

title: chicken with sweet and sour sauce
directions: Make sauce before starting chicken.
Bring water and sugar to boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Add vinegar.
Cook 1 minute more. Meanwhile, blend cornstarch and soy sauce with a little cold water to make a paste.
Stir in to thicken sauce.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Lay rice on bottom of pan, then chicken.
Sprinkle with onion soup; over this pour mushroom soup mixed with water.
Sprinkle with garlic, if desired.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°, covered.

title: watergate salad
directions: Do not drain pineapple; add all ingredients together and chill.

title: breakfast casserole or breakfast burritos
directions: Scramble eggs and mix in as many ingredients as you like, green chilies, Ro-Tel, olives, mushrooms and onions. Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with shredded hash browns, then layer your cooked and drained sausage, then put the egg mixture on top of the sausage layer.
Top it off with the cream of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle grated cheese on as you are adding the layers and save some for the top.
Cook at 375° for 40 minutes or until done. Eat as a casserole or with tortillas.

title: scalloped pineapple bread pudding
directions: Combine eggs,
sugar and butter in large bowl.	Fold in crushed pineapple
and
bread
cubes.
Pour
into buttered 9 x 12-inch baking
pan,
Pyrex is best.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fudgy mint brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray an 8-inch square pan with vegetable cooking spray.
With an electric mixer, beat the egg white until soft peaks form.
Transfer to a small bowl.
Put the sugar and margarine into the mixer and beat until crumbly.
Add water, vanilla and egg.
Beat at low speed until well blended. Combine the flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to the sugar mixture on low speed, beating just to blend.
Stir in crushed candy.
Stir half the beaten egg white into the batter.
Fold in the rest of the egg white.
Transfer the batter to the prepared pan and bake about 22 to 25 minutes or until brownies test done.
Cool on a rack.
Just before serving, sprinkle the powdered sugar over the brownies through a sieve.

title: applesauce cake (low calorie)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into bundt pan and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: soup
directions: Cook beef and onions together until done.
Cook rice and rinse.
Mix all together and let simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Very good in cold weather.

title: pimento spread
directions: Boil 10 minutes and seal in jars.

title: crab puffs
directions: Slice English muffins and quarter.
Mix all other ingredients with electric mixer and spread on quarters.
Freeze for 30 minutes.
Take out of freezer and place under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: crustless leek and potato quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch quiche dish or pie pan; set side. In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, melt butter. Add leeks, potato, salt and pepper and cook, stirring for 1 minute.
Add the water and simmer, covered, for 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: applesauce jellied mold
directions: Heat applesauce until bubbly. Stir in and dissolve jellos. Stir in Sprite (fill foam up), orange peel and juice. Chill until partially set. Add chopped apple and nuts. Turn into greased mold. Chill until firm.
Turn on plate and decorate with sugared green and purple grapes, if desired.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, letting butter melt in iron skillet. Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into hot skillet; bake for 45 minutes, or until brown.

title: cracker 'n vegetable lasagna(makes 6 servings)
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook and stir red pepper, onion, zucchini and oregano in margarine until tender.
In lightly greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, layer half each of crackers, vegetable mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese. In bowl, beat milk and egg product.
Evenly pour over cheese layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: manicotti with beef and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ground beef, sausage and bread crumbs in large bowl.
Carefully stuff noodles.
Boil in 6 quarts water.
Cook until noodles are tender, yet firm.
Pour 1/2 jar of spaghetti sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Layer noodles in pan.
Cover with mushrooms, onions, olives and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour remaining sauce over cheese.
Cook for 45 minutes. Cover with remaining cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: cheese strata
directions: Butter bread and cube it.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with bread.
Grate cheese.
Layer cheese and meat twice, ending with meat on top.
Beat eggs and milk with dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over other ingredients; cover with foil. Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wine cake
directions: Grease	and
flour a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with pecans.

title: blueberry yogurt pancakes
directions: Beat eggs in medium bowl with mixer until fluffy.
Beat in remaining ingredients just until blended.
Grease heated griddle if necessary.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie mix on pizza pan.
Cook according to directions. Combine Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Allow cookie to cool, then spread mixture on and arrange fruit.

title: cajun dirty rice(dressing)
directions: In large pot with lid on low heat, put in oil and onion.
Stir until onion is a rich brown.
Add water to stop browning.
Put in all the meat.
Stir every 10 minutes until brown.
Add hot sauce, salt, pepper and wine.
Cover and put on medium heat, stirring every 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook for 3 hours; add more water if needed.
Uncover and cook until firm.
Turn off heat.
Add parsley and onion tops; stir.
Add cooked rice and serve.
Serves 4 hungry Cajuns or a family of 6 to 8.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add the vegetable soup and reduce heat.
Let the mixture simmer.
Make the mashed potatoes as indicated on box for 12 servings.
When the potatoes are done, remove the ground beef and vegetable soup mixture from the heat.
Use a cake pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Pour the beef and vegetable soup in cake pan to create an even layer. Next spoon the mashed potatoes on top to create another layer. Smooth it out a little.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top and bake until cheese melts.

title: peach crisp
directions: Put peaches in baking pan.
Sprinkle mixture of cake mix, brown sugar, nuts and oleo over peaches.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Add 2/3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon at a time.
Fold in 1 cup chocolate morsels. Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in oven. Turn oven off; leave until morning.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into pan with hot oil. Brown on both sides.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute garlic and onions in margarine until tender. In a large pot mix all together and cook 1-1/2 hours on a low, low heated simmer.

title: amaretto cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Mix well.
Put in bottom and side of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In same bowl, beat cream cheese, 3 eggs and sugar until smooth.
Add reserved cake mix, almond and lemon juice, milk and Amaretto.
Reserve 1/3 of cream cheese mix.
Pour remaining into crust.
Mix chocolate into remaining cheese mix and pour over cheese in pan, cutting with a knife to make marble effect.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: stuffingburgers
directions: Combine stuffing mix, milk and onion.
Let stand 10 minutes. Mix with beef, salt and pepper.
Make 4 to 5 patties.

title: macaroni puff
directions: Pour the hot milk over the bread crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 cup of cheese and add remaining to milk mixture; cover and let stand until cheese melts.
Add cooked macaroni, egg yolks, pimiento, butter, parsley, onion and salt.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff, but not set.
Fold into macaroni mixture. Pour into an ungreased baking or souffle dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven about 50 minutes or until set.
Top with remaining cheese and return to oven until melted.
Serve immediately.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In separate container, mix water, vinegar and egg, then add to dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly and chill for 1/2 hour. Roll out for desired pastry crusts.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix 3/4 of onions and all other items and pour into baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Layer on lettuce, tomato, cheese and olives. (Olives are optional or serve on the side.)
Use tortilla chips to dip in and eat.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed and drain.
Add mushroom soup and cheese and place on top of vegetables in casserole dish.
Top with bread cubes.
Melt butter and pour over bread cubes.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage lasagna
directions: Saute turkey, onion, bell pepper and garlic in skillet sprayed with nonstick spray.
Boil cabbage in water, covered, just until tender-crisp.
Reserve 1 cup cabbage liquid and add with tomato paste, mushrooms, Italian seasoning, basil, parsley, red pepper, salt and pepper to meat mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
In a 9 x 9 x 2-inch square casserole, layer half meat mixture, drained cabbage and remaining meat mixture.
Top with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cut into 6 serving squares.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preheat oven 350°
Cream butter and add sugar gradually, beating until light.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Beat in honey, add sifted dry ingredients alternately with the milk and beat only until smooth. Stir in nuts and fruits fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and pour into 9 X 5 X 3 loaf pan lined on
the bottom with wax paper.
Bake 1 hour. or until done.
Cool cake in pan for 5 minutes.
Turn cake out on a rack and peel off paper. Turn cake right side up to cool. Look up the references in the old testaments
except for
1 Cor. You will find that in the New Testament.

title: fancy eggs
directions: Melt butter in hot skillet.
Cut hole in middle of slice of bread with a glass.
Put bread in skillet and add egg to center of bread.
Cook on both sides to desired doneness of egg.
Very good! Hard to eat just one.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Cook hen until tender, cool and slice.
Cook noodles as directed on box.
Cook celery until tender in about 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Blend this with your soup.
If frozen chicken is used and you don't have broth, cook celery in water.
Drain, add to soup and then dilute soup with 1 cup milk.
In a greased casserole, put layer of noodles and remainder of soup.
Add small amount of sherry.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Cook at about 350° until bubbly.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Combine first eight ingredients and spread in a shallow baking dish- 8 inch x 12 inch.
Top with crackers and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350 degree oven.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Season with salt, pepper and Accent to taste.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake about 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut with peas(kapusta i grock)
directions: Soak peas 10 to 12 hours.
Cook in same water one hour.
Rinse and squeeze dry the sauerkraut, then chop and cover with water. Bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms and onion and cook for one hour. Add peas and cook for 1/2 hour.
Blend in butter, salt and pepper.

title: vegetarian fettuccini
directions: Heat oil in a 12-inch nonstick skillet.
Saute broccoli, celery, onion, garlic, basil and mushrooms for 5 minutes over medium-high heat.
Add the milk, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Heat just to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: butter
directions: Pour whipping cream into 6 small baby food jars.
Screw lids on very securely.
Shake vigorously until thick and pale yellow. Drain off any whitish liquid and save it for tasting.
Salt the butter and serve on crackers, flapjacks or hot biscuits.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Clean potatoes, slice, but not completly through.
Place in baking dish.
Spread mixture over and bake for 10 minutes in microwave.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Makes soft dough.
Drop dumplings from spoon into hot broth.
Cover and steam for 12 to 15 minutes without lifting cover.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit well and mix.
Put in baking dish.
Melt butter, stir in sugar and curry powder powder.
Pour over fruit.
Bake uncovered in 300° oven for 1 hour.
Serve as a relish or side dish.
Great with ham or pork roast.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: In a large bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
In a small bowl, mix egg, bananas, milk and oil. Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened. Spoon batter into greased muffin cups. Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: okra casserole
directions: If using frozen okra, let thaw on a paper towel until all water runs out.

title: pk special steak
directions: Place the steak on a floured board and cover with a coating of flour. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and pound, pound, pound! Turn the meat over several times during this tenderizing process, adding another thin layer of flour each time. The more flour you pound into it, the better the end result will be. Cut the meat into serving portions and fry in hot oil until brown and crispy. Remove each piece to a serving platter and cover to keep it hot. The steak may also be placed in a crockpot with a small amount of water to keep it hot. Makes 4-6 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together until smooth.
Fold in 3/4 of the Cool Whip.
Pour into the pie crust.
Frost with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Use 9 x 12 pan, ungreased. Spread and mix pineapple and cherry pie filling together. Then pour cake mix on top of mixture. Spread out. Add pecans. Melt butter and pour on top of cake mix.

title: chicken canabury
directions: Take 2 sets of chicken breasts and debone and flatten between two pieces of wax paper. Spread on chicken breasts the salt and pepper, Dijon hot mustard, mozzarella cheese and Italian seasonings. Roll like a jelly roll and fry about 3 minutes on each side in 1/2 pt. of olive oil. Take 3 fresh tomatoes, cut-up, 1/2 pt. mushrooms sliced, 1 bunch of green scallions, cut-up and a 1/2 pt. of vermouth or 1/2 pt. sherry cooking wine. Set chicken aside and put the rest of the ingredients in olive oil and simmer 3 minutes. Put chicken on top of all the ingredients and cook 5 minutes more on medium temperature.

title: glazed graham crackers
directions: Mix butter, oleo and sugar together.
Cook over medium heat, stirring for 3 minutes.
Layer crackers in pan with sides (single layer of crackers).
Pour glaze over crackers.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes. Take up on wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken cubes in bottom of 9 x 11-inch casserole dish. Mix all other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake in a 450° oven for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and cut into bite size pieces. Mix mayonnaise, soup, onion, celery and broth. Add chicken.
Place 1/2 package of stuffing mix on bottom of pan; spread mixture on top. Top with rest of stuffing mix; bake at 350° for about an hour or until it is bubbly and brown on top.
Use a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar together.
Cut biscuits in quarters. Roll in the cinnamon mixture.
Drop in greased pan (I use a Bundt pan).
Drop pecans between and on top.
Bring margarine and brown sugar to a boil and pour over the biscuits.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes and then turn out of pan.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, add soups and milk.
Stir.
Add boned chicken in small pieces, onion and green chillies; heat well. Spray oblong baking dish.
Alternate layers:
tortillas, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes covered.
Can top with sliced black olives.
Serve with chopped lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and picante sauce.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients including chocolate flavor packet; stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: ranger cookies(granola)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the first 5 ingredients thoroughly, then stir in the remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased sheet; bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Stir in diced potatoes.
Simmer and cover 15 minutes.
Mix vinegar, sugar and water together.
Pour half of mixture over potatoes.
Let simmer off.
Stir often.
Pour rest of mixture over potatoes and let simmer off again (uncovered).
Stir often.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll steak in mixture and lightly brown both sides in grease.
While cooking steak, saute onion, green pepper and mushroom in butter in a saucepan.
When tender, add cream of mushroom soup.
When steak is brown on both sides, layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In grease from brown steak, add flour and milk to make a little bit of gravy.
Add this to onion, green pepper, etc.
mixture.
Stir.
Pour this over steak and cover with Reynolds Wrap.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes at 350° until steak is tender.

title: lemon lust
directions: Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Bake in 2 loaf pans or angel food pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces; put in warm skillet with oil. Add Worcestershire sauce, onion, pepper and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Combine cake mix and dry pudding mix.
Add Wesson oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, then 7-Up and mix well.
Bake in 3 layers for 40 minutes or until done at 325°.

title: baked fresh salmon
directions: Split fish in half lengthwise and salt and pepper to taste. Place in a baking pan.
Saute margarine, onion and mushrooms.
Add lemon juice.
Pour sauce over salmon and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Easy and delicious!

title: harvest fruit salad
directions: Cover fruit with cold water and simmer gently, covered, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add sugar for the last 5 minutes.
Drain the fruit and reserve the syrup.
Add cold water to reserved syrup to make 1 1/2 cups.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in the reserved syrup.
Chill until partly set.
Pit prunes; cut up all fruit into small chunks.
Fold in to gelatin mixture.
Pour into mold and chill several hours.
Serves 8.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Blend crumbs, 3/4 cup peanut butter and butter in large bowl with fingers, until well blended.
Press mix firmly into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle crust with 1 tablespoon of the chocolate syrup.
Freeze to set crust, 15 minutes.	Swirl together ice
cream, remaining peanut butter and 1 tablespoon syrup. Mixture does not need to be completely blended.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze
until ice cream is very firm, at least 4 hours. Drizzle each serving with some of the remaining syrup.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix flour, salt and margarine.
Add pecans and press down in sheet cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Just before serving,
add
plenty of crumbled, cooked and crisp bacon.

title: king louie's fruit salad
directions: Drain grapefruit and pineapple and place in a small bowl. Peel the bananas and cut them into penny slices.
Put them in a bowl with the fruit.
Pour in the orange juice and lemon juice. Stir gently.
Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and put it in the refrigerator to chill for 1 hour.

title: quick coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease baking sheets.
Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon 1 inch apart on prepared baking sheet. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from baking sheet at once.
Cool on racks.
Makes about 24 macaroons.

title: lemon dill fish
directions: Stir mayonnaise, lemon juice and peel, and dill until well blended.
Place fish fillets on greased rack of broiler pan. Brush with half of the sauce.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes; turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Continue broiling 5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked peaches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel, halve and pit peaches.
In 1-quart saucepan, over medium high heat, heat sugar, lemon juice, butter and water to boiling.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Place peaches in a 3-quart casserole. Add syrup, cover and bake 30 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Place a little mint jelly in each half if you like.
Serve, drained, as a garnish for a meat dish or as a dessert.

title: scott's favorite dessert that i never make
directions: First Layer:
Place first 3 ingredients in pan.
Cut butter into thin squares and place on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° until butter is melted.
Cool completely.
Second Layer:
Mix all ingredients until smooth, and pour over crust.
Third Layer:
Mix pudding according to directions on box, add Cool Whip and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, beat eggs with fork.
Gently fold in the Cool Whip, graham cracker crumbs, apples, 1/4 cup corn syrup, cinnamon and nutmeg until blended. Spread evenly in pan.
Mix remaining corn syrup, walnut pieces and margarine.
Spoon evenly over batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool in pan.

title: punch
directions: Stir together and freeze.
Thaw to mush.
Add 2 quarts ginger ale.
Serves 50.

title: no bake pudding cake
directions: In a deep E-Z foil pan, layer one row of the sponge cookies. Prepare the chocolate instant pudding as directed on box.
Pour over layer of cookies.
Place another layer of cookies over the chocolate pudding.
Prepare the vanilla instant pudding as directed on box.
Pour over the second layer of cookies. Spread Cool Whip over the vanilla pudding, covering completely. Decorate with cherries or nuts. Refrigerate.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slice potatoes.
Mix ingredients, except potatoes, in bacon grease.
Mix well.
Add potatoes and heat.
Crumble bacon over top before serving.

title: play clay
directions: Stir together baking soda and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add water and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture is the consistency of moist mashed potatoes, turn out on a plate and cover with a damp cloth.
When cool enough to handle, knead like dough, then make whatever you want.
Store in tightly closed plastic bag in refrigerator for later use.
Great for a rainy day for "kids."

title: slush
directions: Blend coconut in blender.
Mix all and freeze.
Take out 1/2 glass.
Fill with 7-Up, etc.

title: orange slush punch
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except 7-Up and freeze until firm. Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.
Break frozen mixture into large pieces and put in punch bowl.
Add 7-Up and stir until slushy.
Makes 6 1/2 quarts.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in boiling water and then add the cold water.
Cool the Jell-O and then add the cottage cheese and pineapple, drained.
Refrigerate to set.
Serves 6 people.
Can decorate with cherries, if desired.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix last 7 ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes or until tested done when a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: cherry winks
directions: Cream sugar, butter, eggs and juice together, then add to dry mixture. Then add chopped cherries and nuts. Place heaping teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet; top with cherry half. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: texoma beans
directions: Chop
onion; saute in bacon drippings.
Add ground beef and brown.
