Mix in Ro-Tel tomatoes, green chilies, chili powder, cumin, oregano and garlic powder; salt and pepper to taste.
Add cooked red beans.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve with Mexican corn bread.

title: apple treat
directions: Pour the applesauce, chopped nuts, raisins, nutmeg and cinnamon into a bowl and mix.
Put in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla, blend well. Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon.
Stir in nuts. Spoon batter into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8 pan.
Bake 325° for 1 1/2 hours or muffins approximately 30 minutes.
Yellow squach may be substituted for zucchini.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Add butter, soup and all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix together and stir over medium heat until it thickens. Pour into baked pie crust. Top with Cool Whip.

title: baked ham with plum sauce
directions: For sauce, in a small saucepan stir together plum preserves, brown sugar, vinegar, onion, garlic, red pepper and ginger.
Bring mixture to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove mixture from heat.

title: party mix
directions: Mix Chex, pretzels, mixed nuts, Cheerios, crackers, Honeycomb cereal, Fritos and peanuts in a 20-quart stainless steel bowl. Melt oleo and put seasoning salt and Worcestershire sauce in with oleo.
Mix, then pour over cereals.
Preheat oven to 250° and bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container or glass jars.
It also freezes well.

title: chopped liver
directions: Fry liver and onion over low heat in a covered pan until done (no longer pink on inside), about 20 minutes.
Grind liver, onion and juice remaining from frying and eggs in meat grinder.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: oregano chicken breasts
directions: Trim off any excess fat and skin from chicken.
Sprinkle with flour and oregano, shaking off excess.
Dip in milk; sprinkle with flour and oregano again.
Spread lemon rind lightly onto skin side of chicken breasts before dipping into egg.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix the sugar, flour and salt in a bowl.
Bring to a boil the oleo, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour mixture.
Beat in the soda, eggs and sour cream.
Pour on greased 11 x 12-inch cookie sheet. Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add eggs. Stir in flour.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
Spread into pie shell.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix peas, corn, celery, green peppers, onions and sugar dissolved in vinegar and salt.
Mix and marinate 24 hours.

title: new mexico bread pudding(10 to 12 servings)
directions: Combine raisins and bourbon in small bowl.
Let stand 1 hour. Drain.

title: beef with dunn dumplings
directions: Add salt and pepper to flour and coat stew meat.
Brown stew meat in oil.
Add onions; saute until tender.
Pour can of cream of chicken soup and 1 can of water over stew meat; simmer until tender.
Pour in baking dish.
Layer biscuits on top of stew meat and soup mixture and brown.

title: hot chef's salad
directions: In large skillet, combine dressing and sugar.
Heat to boiling.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; let set until cool.
Mix the cream cheese with a small amount of pineapple juice.
When well blended, add pineapple, cranberry juice and nuts, then let set until firm.

title: a.v. porter's rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt and yeast.
Then add eggs, mix well.
Add milk. Melt Crisco and add to mixture.
Mix real good.
Then sift 4 cups flour.
Mix 3 cups first, mixing well.
Then add 2 more cups. Work with hands until smooth.
Sift flour on paper or cloth. Divide dough in half.
Take half roll on floured paper, stretch or roll it out long.
Cut in small pieces.
Add a dab of butter in each and roll it up.
Put rolls in buttered pan (8 to 9-inch). Smear melted butter on top of patted down rolls.
Let set out to rise before cooking.
Cook on 350° until brown.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add oil, vanilla, eggs, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Mix together thoroughly.
Bake in 10-inch greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese crisp cookies
directions: Mix grated cheese and margarine.
Beat slowly.
Add flour; mix well.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Roll in small balls and mash flat with fork.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: oven stew
directions: Shake beef cubes in paper bag with flour.
Place beef on bottom of 2 1/2-quart covered casserole baking dish.
Put potatoes and carrots on top of beef.
Sprinkle with Lipton soup.
Mix 1 can tomato soup with 1 can water and pour over beef and vegetables. Cover with tight lid.
(Frozen peas may also be added.)
Bake in 300° oven for three hours without removing lid.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together and make into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: joyce's bean salad
directions: Refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.
Salad will keep in refrigerator 1 week.

title: crumb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; form into ball.
Place half of dough into greased pie plate.
Add filling.
Make crumbs with rest of dough, then sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Combine sugars, flour and oatmeal.
Cut in peanut butter.
Add egg, vanilla and butter.
Mix well.
Press into a well-greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with icing.

title: german dressing
directions: Mix and shake well.
Add 1 cup Wesson oil and shake well again.
Keep in refrigerator and shake before each use.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: pretend soup
directions: Whisk together.
In each bowl add 5 slices banana and 2 tablespoons of berries.
Ladle soup over fruit and eat.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put melted margarine into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Whisk together; then mix with milk. Pour over butter.
Pour pie filling over the batter.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease and flour two loaf pans
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into pans and bake for one hour.

title: orange crush
directions: Set ice cream out at room temperature several hours before preparation.
When partially melted, blend all ingredients together and serve chilled.
Garnish glasses with fresh strawberries or orange slices.
Makes 25 to 30 servings.
Great for brunch.

title: pecan shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all of the ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
When well blended, pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Prick top with a fork.
Bake 40 minutes. Remove and place on wire rack to cool and harden.
Cut into squares.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter and eggs well.
Add vanilla.
Add mixed dry ingredients and blend well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: white chocolate krispie treats
directions: During the latter half of the 19th century, one of the magnificent sights of the fire service was that of a team of gallant fire horses, riding artillery style, pulling a smoke-belching nickel-plated steam pumper or ladder truck to a fire.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add warm water, lemonade, nectar and pineapple juice.
Stir well. Add 1/2 gallon cold water. Freeze in 4 equal size containers.
Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
Allow punch to thaw to a slushy consistency. Add 1 part ginger ale to 1 part of slushy punch as needed to serve.
Serves 40.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: In saucepan, combine water, vegetables, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Do not drain. In a large saucepan, melt butter. Stir in flour, then milk and heat to boiling. Continue simmering, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add Cheddar cheese; stir until melted. Add undrained vegetables and ham, if used. Heat through but do not boil. If desired, add cooked broccoli.

title: sandy's zucchini(serves 4)
directions: Parboil zucchini.
Halve lengthwise.
Combine mayonnaise, Bleu cheese and garlic salt.
Spread on zucchini.
Top with grated Parmesan.
Broil until bubbly 5 to 10 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Let cook until bubbling, then put in onion rings on top. Brown, but do not burn.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, cheese, sugar and flour.
Stir well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Then pour melted margarine over top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking soda, salt and egg in bowl. Add bananas and melted margarine. Stir well. Pour into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green rice
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped broccoli.
Cook 5 minutes. Saute celery and onion in oleo until tender. Add soup and Cheez Whiz to broccoli. Add rice, celery and onion.
Place in covered casserole dish and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sunday chicken rice bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange pieces of 2 1/2 or 3 pound broiler/fryer chicken over top.
Pour the 1/2 cup reserved mushroom soup over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with aluminum foil sealed tightly around edges.
Bake at 375° (glass:
350°) until rice is tender, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: overnight seven layer salad(prepare the night before)
directions: Put lettuce, onion, bacon, cauliflower, and peas in layers in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread the mayonnaise on top.
Then sprinkle with the cheese.
Cover the bowl tightly and refrigerate.
Toss before serving.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of ham, potatoes, onions, salt, pepper and grated cheese in casserole; repeat.
Spoon soup over top (undiluted). Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or 4 hours on high.

title: cinnamon pancake syrup
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in pan.
Gradually stir in water.
Cook until clear, 4 or 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon.

title: quick peach cobbler(makes one 9 x 13-inch pan)
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan in preheated oven.
Combine milk, flour and sugar.
Add to melted butter.
Do not stir.
Add peaches to this and do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until browning occurs.

title: strawberry-glazed ham
directions: In a saucepan, combine strawberry preserves and cornstarch. Add lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and is bubbly.
Set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Roll in ball. Roll in chopped nuts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Note:
If you have any chocolate chips, nuts, raisins or coconut, put some in.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans well.
Thin soup with milk.
Blend the soup with 1/2 of the onions.
Lay in well-greased casserole dish.
Add the remaining onions.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Slowly bring
milk, sugar and butter to a boil, and boil until a
ball
forms
when
dropped into cold water; do not let scorch. Remove
from
heat and stir in chopped dates and nuts. Beat with a
spoon
until
it
is too hard to move.
Pour onto cheesecloth or
cotton dish towel which has been sprinkled with powdered sugar and
a little cornstarch.
Roll firmly in towel and when completely cooled, unroll and cut into slices.

title: old fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until it spins a thread or hard ball.
Add peanuts and butter.
Cook until it turns a gold brown, stirring constantly (careful not to scorch it).
Remove from fire and add vanilla, salt and soda.
Mix quickly and pour into buttered foil-lined cookie sheets.
Mixture will be extremely hot. Allow to cool completely; peel off the foil, then break into chunks.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into loaf pans.
Make loaf pans 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: special k roast
directions: Mix altogether
and
place
in
9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spiced hot tea
directions: Mix and store.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: german sweet chocolate pudding pie
directions: Heat spread, sugar, coconut and pecans in small saucepan until spread and sugar are melted and mixture comes to boil.
Boil 30 seconds.
Spread on bottom of pastry shell.
Stir pudding mix into milk in medium saucepan.
Add chocolate.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour over coconut mixture.
Place plastic wrap on surface of pudding mixture. Refrigerate 4 hours.
Remove plastic wrap and garnish as desired.

title: spaghetti and meatballs a la berry
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients together in large saucepan and simmer.
In a mixing bowl, combine ground beef, 1 onion, bread crumbs, egg and seasonings together and form meatballs.
Dice 2 onions in skillet with olive oil and lay meatballs on top of onions; simmer 15 minutes, turning balls gently.
Pour meatballs, oil and onions into sauce and continue simmering.
After sauce thickens, serve over spaghetti.

title: appetizer snack
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: very good grouse
directions: Wash the grouse; cut legs and thighs off in one piece.
Remove back but keep breast whole.
Flour gently; salt and pepper.
Saute in butter.
Put in casserole.
Add celery and mushroom soups, whipping cream and mushrooms.
Cover.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jello ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in fruit.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.
Dissolve 1 package gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in ice cream.
Pour over gelatin in mold.
Chill until thickened.
May use Cool Whip as garnish.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, sugar, baking powder and baking soda. Cut in shortening. Combine orange juice and rind with egg. Pour all at once into the dry ingredients, mixing just enough to moisten. Carefully fold in nuts and cranberries. Spoon into greased loaf pan. Spread corners and sides slightly higher than center. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool. Store overnight before cutting. This recipe freezes well and is good for gifts.

title: * deviled egg mold *
directions: Sprinkle gelatine on water to soften.
Place over low heat and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add next 4 ingredients; cool.
Stir in mayonnaise and fold in remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 3-cup mold or individual molds and chill until firm.
Unmold on plate and decorate, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, not browned.
Combine onion, ground beef, beaten egg, green pepper, parsley, salt, pepper and thyme.
Mix well.
Shape in 3/4-inch to 1-inch balls.
Brown meatballs in butter.
Remove from skillet.
Stir flour and beef bouillon granules in skillet; add 3 to 4 cups water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Season to taste.
Add meatballs to gravy.
Cover; simmer about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serves 5 or 6.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Beat water and shortening together.
Mix dry ingredients and sift into liquid ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into 2 circles and place in pans.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 450° or follow instructions for unbaked shells.

title: gingerbread men cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add molasses, egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add gradually.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Decorate with raisins, M&M's, red hots, etc.
Place on cookie sheet lined with parchment paper. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: spice bars
directions: Beat well together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add cinnamon, soda, salt and flour, then add small jars of baby food.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Use jelly roll pan, flour and grease.

title: italian meat loaves
directions: Soak cracker crumbs in milk; add remaining ingredients except catsup.
Mix well.
Shape in 6 individual loaves; place in shallow baking pan or jelly roll pan.
Spread catsup over loaves; sprinkle with a small amount of additional Romano cheese and basil.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Then simmer 20 minutes.
Crush chips in bowl, add soup, sprinkle with grated cheese and sour cream.

title: papaya mango relish
directions: Toss all ingredients together in a bowl. Set aside for 1 hour to blend flavors. Serve with grilled chicken or fish.

title: hearty chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Saute celery, carrots and garlic in olive oil. Stir in chicken and cook for about 2 minutes.
Add Cavender's seasoning and crushed fennel seeds.
Mix water with chicken bouillon cubes and combine with veggies and bay leaves. Simmer for about an hour.
It's great with cornbread.
It's also good for colds!

title: peaches 'n cream cake
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in a large mixer bowl, beating at medium speed.
Pour into greased 9 or 10-inch deep dish pie pan.
Drain peaches, but save the juice.
Place peach slices over the batter in pan.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger with garlic and finely chopped onion to taste. Roll into small meatballs.
Fry on low heat until done.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to cream mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 well-greased 8-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lamb romanoff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare noodles as directed on package except increase milk to 2/3 cup.
Stir in remaining ingredients except paprika.
Pour into an ungreased 1-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake until lamb is hot, about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: cream fondue
directions: Mix all ingredients, chill.
Serve as a dip for fresh strawberries, peaches or pears or drained canned mandarin sections.

title: smoked sausage and potato casserole
directions: In large pan, saut onions and butter or margarine over medium heat until brown.
Stir in water, chopped sausage and potatoes.
Continue to stir until potatoes are fully cooked.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Spread Cheddar cheese evenly across top of mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Set the first 4 ingredients slightly.
Whip in cottage cheese, mayonnaise, onion and celery.
Add spinach.

title: cherry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Combine vegetables well.
Beat remaining ingredients until fluffy.
Fold in vegetables allow to chill several hours.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, eggs and buttermilk; beat well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into shortening mixture.
Mix pecans, cherries and dates.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet, spacing about an inch apart.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Store in tight container.
Will keep for weeks.

title: snakie's booze balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar and refrigerate overnight before serving.
Keep refrigerated!

title: pomanders
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water with sugar and syrup and water. Stir till fully, mixed and sugar is melted.
Remove from heat and stir in orange extract.
Quickly mix in wafers and nuts.
(Have them ready first, mixed together.)
Form into small balls and roll in sugar.
Let cool thoroughly.
Store in covered container for 3 to 4 weeks.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: chuck wagon steak
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Make hamburger into large flat patties.
Dip patties in egg-milk mixture, then turn on both sides in cracker crumbs.
Fry in about 1/4-inch hot oil over medium heat, browning both sides.
Serve hot.

title: un-fried crabcakes
directions: Spray lite vegetable oil cooking spray over baking sheet 3 times to coat well.
In a large bowl, combine all remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup of bread crumbs and stir in crabmeat. Using 1/4 cup for each crabcake, form mixture into 8 cakes.
(If mixture is too dry to hold together, add milk a tablespoon at a time.)
Roll cakes in reserved bread crumbs and place on cookie sheet.
Coat cakes lightly with oil spray.
Bake on bottom shelf of oven 15 minutes, turning over once at 7 minutes.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Let cool slightly.
In large bowl mix rest of ingredients together.
Add melted chocolate mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch peanut butter pie
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine pudding mix and gelatin; add milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Add peanut butter and stir to combine; remove from heat and let cool to room temperature.
Spread pudding mixture over prepared crust.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled (about an hour).
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: margaret's chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, mushrooms, pecans and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and salt.
Toss lightly. Chill thoroughly.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Place broccoli in bottom of deep baking dish.
Place boned chicken or turkey on top of broccoli.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and whipping cream.
Pour on meat.
Cover ingredients with Cheese Biscuits.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; beat in egg and vanilla, then add mixed dry ingredients.
Fold in rhubarb and spread into 9
x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle on nuts and cinnamon sugar; bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla, apples, water and oil.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased and floured. Sprinkle butterscotch bits over batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: bandito beans
directions: Cook onion in oil until done.
Add picante sauce, molasses and mustard.
Add beans.
Cook until well blended.

title: grilled parmesan tomatoes
directions: Heat broiler.
Spray baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Arrange tomato halves on baking sheet.
Sprinkle parsley and pepper over tomatoes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Broil 5 inches from heat for approximately 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 (1/2 tomato per serving).
Each serving contains 39 calories, 3 g protein, 1.8 g fat, 5 mg chol. and 11 mg sodium.

title: spicy marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and add chicken or pork chops, ribs or tenderloin.
Marinate at least 1 hour.
Baste while cooking.

title: dumplings
directions: Add first 4 ingredients to flour for stiff dough.
Roll out and cut into
strips.
Put
in
hot
broth, few at a time; cook until done.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Drop from a teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes or until done.

title: dump cake #2
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Put in pineapple, cherry pie filling and yellow cake mix, just as it comes from the package.
Top with pecans and dot with butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: onion pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter and press into 8-inch deep dish pie pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until set.
Serve warm with a variety of crackers.
Can be made a day ahead.
Double recipe for a party.

title: savory corn muffins
directions: Bake according to mix or recipe directions.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Parboil chicken (if grilling).
Cool chicken and place in pan. Pour sauce over chicken.
Marinate several hours.
Place on grill 20 minutes or until done.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and cook, stirring, until thick.
Place chicken in baking dish or pan and sprinkle with salt.
Pour half of sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken and cook, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Remove cover and cook 1/2 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together with mixer and pour over cake mix. Bake in oven at 325 degree about 30 - 35 minutes.

title: yorkshire pudding or popovers
directions: Grease muffin tins very generously.
Set tins in refrigerator to chill.
Mix ingredients together with wire whisk or a fork very vigorously until well blended.
Fill the cold tins 1/3 or 1/2 full.
Place in cold oven.
Turn oven to 450° and bake 25 minutes. Insert toothpick into top of each popover after you take them from the oven to release steam.

title: six bean salad
directions: Drain beans and pimiento; add pepper and onion.
Stir well. Pour dressing over mixture.
Refrigerate for 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain and serve.
Save dressing to store leftovers for several days.

title: applesauce breakfast cake
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: almost pay day skillet
directions: Saute onion.
Add bologna or turkey franks and potatoes.
Fry until potatoes are browned.

title: spiced cabbage
directions: In a large Dutch oven, heat oil.
Saute garlic, onion and cabbage.
Remove outer layer of cabbage and wash.
Shred the whole cabbage including the dark green leaves.
Add shredded cabbage to the sauteed vegetables.
Add chicken stock, salt, ginger root, thyme and red pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 12 minutes.
(Be careful not to overcook.
Cabbage should be firm and green, not soggy.) Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken broccoli ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Chop red pepper, broccoli, water chestnuts and onion.
Flake chicken.
Combine all filling ingredients in mixing bowl.
Arrange crescent rolls in a circle on a 15 inch baking stone with bases overlapping in center and points to the outside.
Scoop filling mixture onto widest portion. Fold points of triangles over filling and tuck under base at center. Filling will not be completely covered.
Bake 25-30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour.
Stir in the cream, corn, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until consistency is very creamy and thick.
Stir occasionally.
This dish is best served immediately (it tends to separate if reheated).
Serves 4.

title: hunter's delight
directions: Brown meat and put in a casserole dish.
Mix together soup, water, corn and pepper, mixing well.
Cook noodles, drain and add to soup mixture.
Pour over meat mixture and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for one hour.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse lentils.
Put all ingredients in a large pot.
Add enough water to cover lentils and vegetables.
Cover and simmer approximately 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: southern peanut pie
directions: Beat eggs, then add syrup and sugar.
Continue to beat while adding melted butter.
Stir in vanilla and chopped nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into crust and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: nut crescents
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients and 1 tablespoon water. Stir in flour and nuts. Mix well. Shape into crescents. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool on rack. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: cinnamon bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, nutmeg, milk and vanilla to taste like egg nog.
Pour into casserole and add 4 slices cinnamon swirl bread, broken into pieces.
Push bread down into mixture; add raisins.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place in a pan of water.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: In mixing bowl, add all ingredients to melted margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Press coconut and nuts into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered cake pan.
Mix 1 box German chocolate cake mix as directed and pour over the coconut and nuts.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, salt, onions, celery and peppers.
Allow mixture to stand overnight.
Drain.
Rinse thoroughly and drain again in a colander.
Press bowl down on top of vegetable mixture to force out as much liquid as possible.
In large pot combine rest of ingredients and bring to rolling boil.
Reduce heat and boil gently 20 minutes.
Makes 8 pints.

title: chicken stew(black pot chicken stew; 30 gal)
directions: Cook and debone chicken, saving broth.
Add cut potatoes and onions to broth and chicken in black pot.
Constantly stirring the pot to make sure it doesn't stick.
when potatoes are done add corn and tomatoes.
Keep stirring give stew time to thicken up. Add salt and pepper to taste and macaroni.
Pour up immediately.

title: overnight salad
directions: Put in layers as listed.
Sprinkle sugar and cheese on top. Put Miracle Whip on top by spoonful.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix together before serving.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake and bake according to directions on package. Punch holes in cake and pour cream of coconut over it.
Top with Cool Whip and shredded coconut.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend butter and flour.
Add hot milk and mix well.
Then blend with corn, beaten eggs and sugar.
Use seasonings to your taste if desired.
Bake in casserole at 375° for about 50 minutes or until done in the center.

title: strawfolt (honey clusters)
directions: Heat peanut oil in fryer to 365°.
Place in large bowl 2 c. flour, 1/8 tsp. salt.
Make well in center of flour.
Add three eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Add vanilla - mix well to make a soft dough.
If necessary, add 1 - 2 tablespoons water.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: On each slice of ham, place piece of green onion and strip of cream cheese.
Roll up.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Chill before serving.

title: mushrooms with clam stuffing
directions: Clean and wipe the mushrooms.
Remove and dice the stems. Brush the mushroom caps with lemon juice.
In a large skillet, saute minced scallions in 1/2 stick of butter.
Stir in the minced mushrooms; minced garlic and thyme.
Saute until most of the moisture has evaporated (about 5 minutes).
Stir in drained clams; cracker crumbs, minced parsley and salt and pepper to taste. Arrange the mushroom caps hollow side up in a buttered baking dish. Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Fill the mushrooms with the cream mixture, making mounds.
Brush again with melted butter and bake at 350° until brown, about 5 minutes.

title: harvest apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch, spices and salt; mix with apples.
Roll out less than a half the dough between two pieces of waxed paper.
Turn the dough into a 9-inch aluminum pie pan and fill with the apple mixture.
Scatter red hots over the mixture and dot with butter. Roll out remaining dough.
Moisten the rim of the bottom crust with cold water and cover with the top crust, crimping top to bottom.
Trim off excess pastry.
With a fork, prick holes in the top crust or use a knife to make a small slit for steam to escape. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes, reduce heat to 300° and bake 15 minutes more.
Serve with ice cream or wedge of Cheddar cheese.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add ketchup, mustard and chicken gumbo (no water).
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Great!

title: microwave fudge
directions: In large glass measuring cup, combine chocolate chips and milk.
Microwave on High 3 minutes.
Stir until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread in foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: boiled cake with lemon icing
directions: Boil together for 10 minutes the water, oil, apples, sugar, raisins and dates.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan and bake at 350°
for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: In electric skillet, melt jelly on low heat.
Add fruit.
Pour brandy into center of fruit; heat by stirring.
Light very carefully with match.
Spoon over ice cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice in a bowl.
Add carrot, onion, pepper, cucumber and tomato; mix well.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers, chips or bite size fresh vegetables.

title: sausage, peppers and potatoes
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat and brown sausage.
Remove sausage; cut into 1-inch chunks and set aside. Reserve drippings.
Add peppers and cook, stirring frequently, 2 minutes.

Add potatoes and onion soup mix, blended with water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes. Return sausage to skillet and simmer, covered, an additional 5 minutes or until sausage is done and potatoes are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
In a casserole dish, layer chicken on bottom.
Add cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, milk and sour cream.
Stir.
Crumble crackers on top.
Pour melted margarine over the top.
Cook in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: cincinnati chilli
directions: Do not brown meat; pinch it up and put it into the water. Add all ingredients at one time. Cook 3 hours.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Cut raw potatoes into thin slices to measure about 4 cups. Cook and stir onion in butter in a 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in milk and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Place potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour cheese sauce on potatoes.
Cook, uncovered, in 375° oven for 1 hour.
Mix remaining cheese and the bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cook, uncovered, until brown and bubbly, 20 minutes longer.

title: velvet chicken soup
directions: Heat together chicken broth and chicken pieces. Add a little water to cover chicken completely. Boil for 45 minutes to an hour (until chicken pulls away from the bone). Strain 6 cups of broth. Set aside.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk and salt in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cover pan for 1 minute to allow the steam to wash down the sugar crystals off the sides of the pan.
Uncover.
Insert candy thermometer. Cook until it reaches 236° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat; add butter.
Cool until lukewarm (110°).
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until candy begins to thicken and loses its high gloss.
Turn immediately into a buttered 8 x 3 x 2-inch pan. Score with sharp knife into small squares.
Cool.
Store 2 to 3 weeks in tightly covered container.

title: strawberry cake and icing
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool. Ice cake.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Make dressing the night before baking turkey.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs for one minute at half speed. Add 1 cup flour and beat for 1 minute.
Add 1 cup of milk alternately with rest of flour.
Add flavoring.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Increase heat to 350° and continue baking for 10 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: In large pan, combine water, cabbage, bacon, carrots and potato mix.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 15 minutes.
Combine milk and cornstarch; add to chowder, along with green beans.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: tailgate sandwich
directions: Grate cabbage.
Mix mayonnaise with mustard; mix with cabbage .
Slice loaf in half. Pull out soft insides of each half.
Spread bottom half with 2 teaspoons of mayonnaise.
Layer ham, salami and tomatoes.
Put coleslaw atop.
Place top half over bottom.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, Polish sausage, green pepper, onion and chili powder; then drain.
Add tomato sauce, diced tomatoes, rice, Tabasco sauce and tomato juice.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer to desired consistency.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Set aside.
In pan mix cocoa, oleo and water.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Pour in sugar and flour mixture.
Then add milk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour into large greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, vanilla, zucchini and oil.
Add flour and nuts.
Pour into greased bread pans. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hawaiian icebox cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Increase speed to medium and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into baking pan coated with cooking spray and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Let cool in pan on rack.
Combine milk and pudding mix in bowl and beat at low speed for 2 minutes until thickened.
Cover bowl and chill for 5 minutes.
Stir in pineapple.
Pierce holes in top of cake using handle of spoon.
Spread pudding mixture over cake, then whipped topping.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Eat right away or keep in fridge.
tags: instant banana cream pudding pie mix

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour; mix well.
Add almond extract.
Spread batter, which is very thick, into a jelly roll pan.
Mark off 24 squares; put about 3 cherries and juice in center of each.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; let sit for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fruit cocktail parfait pie
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, reserving syrup.
Pour syrup and water into a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Cut ice cream into several pieces and blend into the hot gelatin until melted.
Chill until partly set.
Fold in fruit; pour into pastry shell.
Chill until set.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: lemon bars
directions: Spread mixture on top of crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until set.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta; drain and chill. Add other ingredients to pasta and serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: spicy whirligig loaves
directions: In a bowl, dissolve the yeast in warm, not hot, water.
Add sugar and salt.
Allow the combined milk, butter and eggs to be lukewarm.
When cooled, add to yeast mixture.
Add enough flour to make a soft ball of dough.
Knead on a floured board until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl.
Oil top of dough.
Cover. Place in oven alongside a saucepan of boiling water.
At intervals, reheat the water to boiling.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread and press together crescent rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan. (May do small square pan for sampling also.)
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: crab melt ways
directions: Cut english muffins in 1/4.
Spread mixture and bake till brown at 350°.

title: buffet meatballs
directions: Mix the ketchup, jelly and lemon juice in a medium saucepan. Heat until bubbling.
Mix the turkey with the oat bran, a little at a time, until the mixture is firm enough to form into walnut-sized balls.
Drop the balls into the bubbling mixture to cook about 30 minutes.
Serve hot with toothpicks to spear the meatballs.

title: easy barbecued chicken
directions: Cut up and season chicken with seasonings.
Place in a large roasting pan or baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Drain broth.
Mix together the barbecue sauce and Coke.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for about 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: pennsylvania dutch green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon grease saving 1 tablespoon.
Add onion and saute.
Blend in cornstarch, salt and mustard.
Stir in liquid from beans and cook until thickened. Blend in vinegar and beans.
Heat again and top with crumbled bacon and slices of hard-boiled egg if desired.

title: kraut salad no. 2
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: crab soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add flour and next 5 ingredients. After heating, add milk and stir until thickened.
Add crab meat and simmer.
In separate saucepan, heat half and half and sherry or wine.
When blended and warm, slowly blend into milk and crab mixture.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.

title: white buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and sift flour with dry ingredients, then add (beat in) egg whites.
Add buttermilk and beat well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut crisps
directions: Lightly butter 13 x 9-inch baking pan; set aside.
In 3-quart saucepan, combine butter, peanut butter and half the chocolate pieces.
Stir constantly over low heat until chocolate melts.
Add marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Stir in cereal and peanuts.

title: easy zucchini italian
directions: In a small skillet, add olive oil, zucchini, onion, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook slow about five minutes and stir. Add tomato sauce and heat five more minutes.
Put into bowl, sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: swiss cheese bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in a pie plate. Sprinkle sliced almonds on top.
Bake at 375 for 15-20 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: pebbles cereal treat
directions: On stovetop melt margarine in 5-quart saucepot on low heat; add in marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal; mix to coat.
Press firmly into greased, foil lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan; cool.
Turn onto cutting surface; peel off foil. Cut into squares.
Yield:
35 squares.

title: fudge bars
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add butter and mix until mixture resembles crumbs.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture. Press remainder in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Add 1 cup chocolate pieces.
Melt; remove from heat.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well.
Spread mixture over baked crust. Combine reserved 1/2 cup crumb mixture and remaining 1/2 cup chocolate pieces.
Sprinkle evenly over chocolate mixture and press lightly.
Bake at 350° or until golden brown.
Cut into bars. Makes 4 dozen bars.

title: seafood alfredo
directions: Fix noodles according to package; add frozen vegetables at beginning point of a boil.
Halfway through cooking, add cut up crab or lobster.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water; mix with cranberry and pineapple.
Refrigerate until set.
Mix pineapple juice with cream cheese; pour on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: cauliflower with lemon-tarragon mayonnaise and cheese crust
directions: Steam whole head of cauliflower for about 15 minutes, until barely done.
Cool slightly.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables and soups together.
Pour into the 2 deep dish pie crusts.
Cover each with regular pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler delight
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Drain 1 can of peaches and arrange peach slices in 9 x 12 baking dish. Pour second can of peaches with the juice over arranged peaches. Swirl in Amaretto. Sprinkle cake mix over top. Cover with slivers (1/8-inch thick) of butter. Cobbler is done when it is bubbling and lightly browned.

title: french market soup
directions: Wash dry beans.
Add water to cover and 1 tablespoon salt. Soak overnight.
Drain.
Add 3 quarts water, ham, bay leaves and thyme.
Cover and simmer 3 hours.
Add other ingredients except chicken and sausage.
Salt may be added to taste.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.
Add sausage and chicken.
Simmer until chicken is done.
Remove chicken; debone and return to pot.
Serve very hot over rice, if you like.

title: meat loaf in the round
directions: Combine meat, 1 cup cheese, bread crumbs, celery, onion, egg and seasoning; mix lightly.
Shape into 9-inch round loaf in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour; pour off drippings.
Pour tomato sauce over meat loaf; top with remaining cheese.
Continue baking 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Beat eggs with fork, add sugar, cooking oil and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients, mix well by hand.
Stir in raisins.

title: "kathleen's" banana bread
directions: Mix the flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mash bananas and add to mix.
Add flour mix and pour into greased (with Pam) loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cheese danish
directions: Spread 1 can of rolls in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Press seams together to form 1 piece of dough.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg yolk with mixer until fluffy.
Spread on top of rolls in pan.
Set pan on top of wax paper or foil and with a knife, trace the shape of the pan.
This will give you a guide for rolling the second can of rolls.
Roll second can of rolls to fit the guide.
Press seams together to avoid mixture seeping through. Invert this dough onto top of cream cheese in pan.
Peel off the wax paper.
Brush top with the other egg yolk.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden.
Cool completely and refrigerate before cutting into squares or triangles.

title: ruth lyons' coffee cake(in honor of hector d. kirk)
directions: Combine margarine, the two sugars and flour.
Mix well and save 1/2 cup for topping.
Add eggs, buttermilk and baking soda. Mix well and then add raisins, coconut and pecans.
Pour into 2 floured and greased round cake pans.
Put reserved dry ingredients on top of batter and press some pecans on top of each coffee cake. Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.

title: two-tone chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan, over low heat, melt semi-sweet chocolate chips with 2/3 cup of condensed milk, 1 tablespoon milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/2 cup walnuts.
Spread evenly into foil-lined 9-inch square pan.

title: tangy dip for fresh fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: pork chops with scalloped potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, melt oleo.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth.
Cook and stir constantly until mixture boils. Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In a skillet, brown pork chops in oil.
Season to taste with additional salt and pepper if desired.
In a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, layer potatoes and onion.
Pour broth over the potatoes and onion. Place pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer or until potatoes are tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well.
Cook over medium heat in heavy saucepan.
Stirring constantly until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Add meringue and brown.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meatball vegetable soup(amounts are for 4 servings.)
directions: Blend the ground beef with the egg, salt and pepper.
Cut green onions into 1/2-inch lengths and set aside.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil, milk and molasses and mix well.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix pudding with milk; add remaining ingredients and spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill overnight.
Serves 12 or more.

title: pineapple-cheese mix
directions: Place drained pineapple in baking dish.
Mix juice, flour and cheese.
Stir into pineapple.
Melt margarine.
Add crushed Ritz crackers to margarine.
Spread over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Particularly good with baked ham.

title: fudge
directions: Melt drops in microwave and stir in peanut butter.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour in dish and let set a few minutes.

title: hot cheese cookies
directions: Cream cheese and butter.
Add other ingredients gradually. Roll into logs.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate or freeze. Slice roll and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Wash all pumpkin off seeds. Put enough salt in small pan to cover bottom; add seeds and enough water to float the seeds. Cook on medium-high until water is almost evaporated. Lay out in single layer on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until dried.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate chip toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large bowl, stir flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg; mix well.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips and the nuts.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of mixture. Press remaining crumb mixture onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour condensed milk evenly over hot crust; top with 1 1/2 cups toffee bits.
Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture and remaining 1/2 cup chips over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup toffee bits.
Cool completely, then cut into bars.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat together sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs and milk, beating well.
Beat in flour, cornmeal, lemon juice and rind.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes until custard is set.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together.
Better if made 6 to 8 hours before use.

title: turtle cake
directions: In a double boiler, combine caramels and 1/3 cup milk.
Melt. Set aside.
Grease and flour pan.
Mix cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup milk and nuts.
Press 1/2 dough in pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips over dough; then spread over with caramel mix.
Crumble rest of dough on caramel.
Cool slightly and then refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts and coconut over bottom of pan.
Prepare cake by directions on box.
Spread cake batter over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar; spoon over mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: horseradish mold
directions: Soften cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Mold and chill several hours.
Much better flavor if chilled overnight or longer.

title: glazed carrot coins
directions: In a quart casserole, combine carrots and orange juice. Cover.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Re-cover.
Microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes or until carrots are tender-crisp.
Let stand 2 minutes.

title: roast beef marinade(very good!)
directions: Sprinkle roast with meat tenderizer and garlic salt.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce in glass baking dish.
Put roast in baking dish; cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Turn roast and wait another 24 hours.
Grill on low for about 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine hash browns, sour cream, soup, cheese, minced onions and ham in a large bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix corn flakes and butter. Put over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Brown together beef and onions.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Spray large, deep pan with nonstick spray.
Add cooked beef and onions to sauce.
Layer into pan, some sauce, 1/2 noodles, cottage cheese, noodles and sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rainbow stew
directions: Spray large crock-pot with cooking spray.

Put pinto beans into pot and cover with water. Add 1 can of soup, roast, second can of soup, tomatoes, green chilies, cumin, garlic and oregano. Cook on low heat 16 to 20 hours. Serve with rice and tortillas, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: percolator punch
directions: Place liquids in percolator. Put sugar and spices in basket of percolator. Perk 10 to 12 minutes. Serve while hot. Yields 12 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix together well, then add 1/2 cup of wine vinegar.
Shake well before each serving.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems and caps from mushrooms.
Mix crab meat, egg, bread or cracker crumbs, dash of salt, garlic salt to taste and Parmesan cheese together.
Stuff mushrooms. Bake in oven at 400° for 10 minutes. Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake again until cheese turns golden brown. Serve.

title: tea cakes
directions: Melt butter.
Stir sugar, butter and shortening together.
Add vanilla, egg and flour.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until bottom of cookies are brown.

title: raisin bran butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in Raisin Bran.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten with tines of fork.
Bake at 375° for approximately 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool on a wire rack.
Yield: 3 dozen, about 2 inches in diameter.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate chicken with sauce several hours or overnight.
Bake in open casserole at 350° for 2 to 3 hours or until sauce thickens.

title: turtles
directions: Melt the caramels and milk.
When melted, stir in pecans. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper and let cool.
Melt dipping chocolate.
Dip caramel clusters in chocolate and return to waxed paper to cool.

title: blender coconut custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in blender.
Blend at low speed 3 minutes.
Pour into a 9-inch greased pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mel's pound cake
directions: Beat together butter, shortening, oil and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternate adding flour and baking powder with milk.
Mix well and add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dumplings
directions: Add yeast in milk with sugar, let rise.
Add flour and salt. Add more flour if needed.
Dice toast and mix in.
Work well again and cover (auto bread maker set in "Manual Mode" may be used to here).
Let rise until double in size.
Form dumplings with hands about size of tennis balls.
Make smooth.
Rise again.
Fill pot of water 1/4 full, bring to boil, add dumplings and let cook, covered, 20 minutes.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Mix yogurt with cornstarch until smooth.
Add horseradish and vinegar.
Cook in top of a double boiler until slightly thickened. Serve over or with broccoli or other vegetables.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute first four ingredients in oil until rice is brown. Add remaining ingredients and cook until rice is tender. Can be made in casserole. If so, sprinkle with Provolone cheese and bake at 400° until cheese is brown and bubbly. Serves 6.

title: oyster pie
directions: Put potatoes in pie crust topped with salt, pepper and butter. Then put oysters and juice in.
Top with crust.
Bake at 375° until crust is lightly brown.

title: pasta soup
directions: Saute onion in olive oil.
Add all ingredients, except pasta. Cook pasta; cool and add to soup.

title: beulah's meat loaf
directions: Mix well hamburger, egg, 1/2 can onion soup, salt, pepper, curry powder, garlic and bread; make a loaf.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first
5 ingredients.
Add remainder of ingredients and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Scrape and slice carrots.
Cook until tender in boiling water. Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add lemon juice and brown sugar. Heat, stirring, until like syrup.
Add drain carrots.
Stir to coat and stir in parsley.
Serves 6.

title: creamed spinach dish
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, stir and top with cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Take out 1/2 cup and mix with the water; set aside.

title: peanut butter melt aways
directions: Mix together butter, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Roll into small balls.
Freeze.
Then dip in paraffin and German sweet chocolate that has been melted together.
Dip balls and place on wax paper.
Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: sausage and cream potatoes
directions: Cut sausage in small pieces.
Chop onion fine.
Mix meat and onion together and fry until done.
Add water to cover and cook 10 minutes.
Cut potatoes into quarters.
Add to meat and season. Cover and cook until potatoes are done.
Make a paste of flour and milk.
Add to mixture and cook until thick.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water.
When dissolved, mix with other ingredients.
Store in a greased covered bowl overnight in refrigerator.
When ready to use, roll out the desired amount. Cut into biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: mushroom cheeseburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet.
Drain.
Put back in skillet and add mushrooms, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and 2 tablespoons Bisquick.
Mix well and set aside.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Add topping.

title: special scalloped potatoes
directions: Saute garlic, shallot and crushed red pepper in butter in a Dutch oven for 2 minutes.
Ad milk, whipping cream, salt and pepper, stirring well.
Add sliced potatoes.
Bring mixture to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown.
Let stand 30 minutes before serving.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook together until about 5 tablespoons liquid remains the raisins and water.
Drain, reserving the liquid.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar and eggs. Stir in the cooled raisin liquid and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in oats and the raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in quick moderate oven (375°).
Makes about 4 to 5 dozen cookies 2 inches in diameter.

title: california peach pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, honey and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat about 30 minutes or until thickened, stirring often.
Add vanilla and 1 tablespoon butter.
Portion into serving dishes.
Blend sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon salt and peaches with the syrup.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 minutes, or until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining butter and brandy.
Spoon over rice pudding. Sprinkle with roasted almonds.
Serve warm or cold, topped with the cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Let rise for 45 minutes. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: raw fondant
directions: Cream butter.
Add enough confectioners sugar to butter to make it stiff enough to handle.
Add coloring and flavor of your choice.
Mold to any shape desired.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix hamburger with rice, onion, eggs, salt and pepper.
Put hamburger mixture into mangos.
Pour tomato soup into big pan and put mangos into soup mixture.
Let come to a boil.
Simmer for around an hour and a half.

title: lemon-lime summer drink with fresh fruits
directions: Combine all first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart pitcher. Stir to dissolve sugar. Add 1 cup fresh berries. Cover and chill overnight. Serve over ice, garnished with lemon, lime slices or mint sprig and berries.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add tomatoes and potatoes, carrots, onion, rice, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: cranberry-pineapple relish
directions: Cook sugar in 1 cup of water; boil for 5 minutes.
Add cranberries and cook until berries pop and until thickened consistency.
Remove from heat and add crushed pineapple; mix well.
If desired, chopped nuts can be added.
Chill and serve.

title: easy potato bake
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add everything else except crumbs; mix well.
(Optional:
Can add a little garlic salt, dill weed, salt and pepper at this point.)
Put mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan; flatten it down.
Top with a thick layer of bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tropical delight
directions: Bring first two ingredients to make syrup.
Cool.
Add last four ingredients.
Mix together and freeze.
Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Blend in blender until thick and frothy.
Garnish with a sprinkling of cinnamon.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix lettuce, tomatoes, onion, beans and cheese together. Before serving, pour dressing on and add Doritos.
Toss.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Unthaw frozen broccoli.
Pour Jiffy cornbread mix in a bowl. Add eggs, onion, cottage cheese and salt.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour mix in the pan and stir so the margarine will evenly be in mix.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: maple oatmeal bars
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and maple syrup. Stir in eggs.
Add vanilla. Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Add to batter. Stir in oatmeal.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven about 35 minutes. Cut into squares while warm.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Saute onion. Blend flour and seasoning. Add water. Stir in vegetables.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Stir until cheese is melted.
Garnish with shredded cheese.

title: pecan drops
directions: Beat egg white until stiff peaks begin to form.
Add brown sugar and pecans.
Fold together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 175° to 200° (ovens vary) for 1 hour.

title: mrs. sanderson's pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and margarine.
Cook on low to medium heat until hot to touch and margarine melts.
Remove from heat and very slowly pour mixture into beaten eggs, stirring constantly as you pour.
Add pecans or walnuts and vanilla.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until pie is not shaky in the center.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Combine graham cracker crumbs, 4 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Mix well and form a crust on the bottom only of a spring-form pan.

title: elephant tracks
directions: Heat milk, butter and sugar to warm stage.
Add lemon rind, nutmeg and beaten eggs, yeast (dissolved in a small amount of warm water), salt and flour.
Let rise once.
Roll out dough as for cinnamon rolls.
Spread with butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up as for jelly roll.
Cut in 1/2-inch sections.
Lay sections in sugar and cinnamon mixture on a wax paper and roll very thin with a rolling pin.
They will be real flat.
Bake at once in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot turnip greens dip
directions: Saute onion and celery, stirring in mushrooms when tender. Set aside.
Cook turnip greens according to directions on package. Combine turnip greens and lemon peel into food processor and combine until smooth.
In top of double boiler, combine sauteed vegetables, pureed turnip greens, soup, cheese, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce, stirring frequently, until well blended and hot.
Serve hot with miniature cornbread muffins.

title: crunchy potato balls
directions: Combine potatoes, ham, cheese, mayonnaise, egg, mustard and pepper.
Mix well.
Add enough flour to stiffen.
Chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in cornflakes.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients.
Form into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and place solid milk chocolate kiss on top of each cookie.
Press down so that the cookie cracks around edge.
Return to oven and bake for 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: easy egg salad
directions: Boil eggs; cool and peel.
Dice eggs into medium size bowl. Add all ingredients and mix well.
Cool in refrigerator about an hour before serving.
Serve on bread with lettuce, tomato and a slice of cheese.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Float strawberries and lemon slices. This recipe is also good with vodka.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and blend in pineapple; add jello when cool. Add pecans and and chill well.

title: range-top "baked" apples
directions: Filling:
Combine raisins, currants, dates or fruit bits, the nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon; set aside.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: When sweet potatoes are cool, peel and cut lengthwise in slices about 1/2-inch thick.
In a buttered 2-quart casserole, alternate potatoes, apples, raisins and brown sugar and seasonings.
Cover and bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chipo casserole
directions: Cook beef with onions; drain fat.
Lower heat on stove and place meat back on stove.
Add cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soup; stir well.
Season to taste with pepper, salt, seasoned salt and garlic powder; stir well and cook for 10 minutes or until bubbly hot.
Add diced green chilies (or 2 small jalapenos, diced, for a hotter flavor).
Layer a casserole dish with chips; place meat mixture on top.
Layer top with chips and then cover with grated cheese.
Microwave for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: quiche
directions: Combine eggs, mayonnaise, milk and cornstarch.
Add to beef, cheese and onions.
Prebake pie shells for 5 minutes; let cool. Fill each and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until center of pie is set.
Based on this recipe it yields 8 slices per pie.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients until dough is stiff.
Roll in wax paper and chill.
Slice and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Heat corn, milk, onion flakes, salt and pepper on top of stove. Before serving, sprinkle browned bacon bits on top; grated cheese is also delicious with this dish.
Serve with soda crackers or garlic bread.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until a doughy mixture.
Roll into balls approximately the size of a quarter to a half dollar. Place on cookie sheet and put into oven preheated to 350°.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Grind orange and raisins; add to mixture.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Bake at 350°.
Pour juice of orange and 1/2 cup brown sugar over cake.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Beat whole eggs and sugar until very light and thick.
Add vanilla.
Add flour to this mixture, 1/2 cup at a time.
Bring milk and margarine to a boil and add directly to dough.
Dough will be runny.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in sheet cake pan.

title: spinach casserole
directions: In greased casserole, put layer of spinach, mushroom, cheese and white sauce; repeat.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over it and pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 375° until bubbly and crumbs are brown.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain thoroughly.
Combine spinach with cottage cheese, salt, Parmesan cheese and eggs and blend thoroughly.
Pour into a greased shallow casserole or 7 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour beets
directions: Cut off beet tops, leaving 2 inches of stems.
Clean well; place in pot and cover with boiling water.
Cook until tender. Slip off the outer skins and dice.
Strain and save 1 cup of the water in which the beets were cooked.
Add sugar, vinegar and butter.
Thicken with 1 tablespoon of cornstarch; cook to the consistency of cream.
Add the diced beets and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat.
(Delicious if you like beets.)

title: doris' pumpkin bran cake
directions: You will need a 5-quart bowl.
Mix bran and eggs.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan that's lightly greased.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift meal and flour together in bowl.
Mix in other ingredients.
Melt the 1/4 cup shortening in bread pan.
Pour mixture in greased pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of casserole.
Mash beans and spread over cream cheese. Cover with layer of green chilies.
Put cheese over all and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and lemon juice. Chill until partly thickened.
Fold in pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm, then spread on topping and grated cheese.

title: mom's waffles
directions: Sift flour with salt and baking powder twice.
Beat egg yolks with sugar.
Add milk and butter.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until flour is moistened.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in preheated waffle iron.
Makes 4 or 5 waffles.

title: morning mix-up
directions: In a large skillet, saute potatoes, ham and onion for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
In a small bowl, beat eggs, salt and pepper.
Add to the skillet; cook, stirring occasionally, until eggs are set.
Remove from heat and gently stir in the cheese.
Spoon onto a serving platter.
Sprinkle with chives.
You may use your own hash brown potatoes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: persimmon bread(lighter side)
directions: Cream together sugar and liquid sweetener.
Add eggs and mix after each addition.
Mix all dry ingredients together, add to mixture.
Add mashed persimmons and crushed pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in loaf pan sprayed with nonstick spray.

title: salad
directions: Mix jello with cottage cheese and pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: anne's baked steak
directions: Mix Worcestershire sauce and catsup; spread on top of steak. Add dots of butter.
Bake in a preheated 500° oven for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Top with grated cheese. Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In a large pan, cook ground beef until done; drain off grease. Add water, potatoes, salt and pepper, then cook until potatoes are done.
Add green beans with water and onion on top of beans and then cabbage, chopped on top of everything else.
Let cook until cabbage is steamed.
Serve with hot rolls and butter.

title: souper enchiladas
directions: In 8-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, fry tortillas one at a time for 2 to 3 seconds on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of the hot oil into 10-inch skillet and cook onion and garlic over medium heat until tender. Stir in soup, meat, water, cumin and hot sauce.
Heat through. Spoon about 1/3 cup soup mixture onto each tortilla and then roll it up.
Arrange filled tortillas in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour taco sauce evenly over enchiladas and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes more.

title: maud's chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk. Bring to a boil.
Stir over medium heat to 238° or soft ball stage.

title: the cat's whiskers punch
directions: Half fill punch bowl with ginger ale.
Add scoops of sherbet to fill the bowl.

title: quick nacho dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in a pie dish.
Top with 1 can Hormel chili.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all other ingredients, beat until smooth.
Add cabbage and carrots; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Be sure slaw sets full 2 hours in refrigerator before serving for full flavor.

title: duchess potatoes
directions: Mix together and
put in pastry bag.
Squeeze on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let set for 1 hour in refrigerator.
Mix remaining ingredients with dressing and let set in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.

title: very good chicken
directions: Layer 1 large package dried beef in 10	x
15-inch pan. Wrap chicken in Sizzlean bacon (remove
chicken	skin).	Layer chicken on top of beef.
Pour over 1 can
cream
of
chicken, celery or mushroom soup and sour cream.
Bake 3
hours at 275° or 2 1/2 hours at 325°, uncovered.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix
together	in
a
large
bowl.
Salt
and	pepper. Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 375°. Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: company potatoes
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter until browned.
Add flour and stir.
Add milk; stir until smooth and thickened.
Add salt and pepper.
Place potatoes in buttered casserole dish.
Pour sauce mixture over potatoes; mix slightly.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend chili sauce, lemon juice, salt, pepper, horseradish and Tabasco sauce.
Fold in sour cream.
Add shrimp (broken in pieces).
Cover and chill.
Use as a dip or spread.

title: grandma janetta kirkpatrick curry's refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, lemon juice and vanilla.
Sift cinnamon, baking soda and flour together.
Hand knead dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Add nuts or chocolate chips.
Roll dough into a 1 1/2-inch diameter log.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate until dough is firm enough to slice or freeze for future use.
Slice and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: my mother's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Salt and let stand 1 hour.
Rinse and drain well.
Mix vinegar, sugar and spices.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Bring to a boil again.
Jar and seal.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Clean and separate cauliflower and broccoli into flowerets. Combine all ingredients except bacon.
After all ingredients have been mixed, crumble bacon over top.

title: betty's butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Divide dough; add red food coloring to 1/2 of dough and twist dough in two parts to make candy cane cookies.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken breast with orange sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine in a large skillet. Brown chicken breasts in skillet over medium heat, turning 2 or 3 times.
Transfer chicken to a shallow casserole, skin side up; set aside.
Add seasonings and flour to hot fat in the skillet and stir to blend until smooth and lightly browned.
Gradually add chicken broth and orange juice, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over low heat until smooth and thickened.
Pour on top of chicken.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cut each orange slice in quarters and place two quarter slices on top of each piece of chicken.
Scatter ginger and orange rind on top.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown onions in butter or margarine; add zucchini.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Drain tomatoes and cut halves.
Combine all ingredients except cheese in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sunday roast
directions: Place roast in foil-lined roasting pan.
Sprinkle generously with Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle onion soup and can of mushroom soup over roast, close foil.
Roast for 1 hour at 300°. Reduce heat to 200°.
Cook 2 to 3 more hours.

title: brandied fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry (sifted) ingredients, then add the applesauce and the Brandied Fruit.
Mix well.
Gradually add raisins, coconut and nuts.

title: barbecue mopping sauce
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Reduce to simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Brush on meat with a clean paintbrush.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, dash of salt and melted butter.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Decorate top with pecan halves.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Stir in coconut.
Cook until thick. Put into deep pre-cooked pie crust.
Top with egg whites; sprinkle with coconut.
Cook until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cloud 9
directions: Beat cream cheese; add 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Prepare Dream Whip; add pineapple, nuts, cherries, vanilla and sugar to cream cheese.
Then fold Dream Whip into cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate.

title: all-american barbecue sauce
directions: Place onion in a 1-quart glass measure.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 2 minutes or until tender. Add remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes. Serve with chicken, pork, beef or lamb.
Yields 2 cups (about 11 calories per tablespoon).

title: auntie erma's raspberry squares
directions: Mix butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Gradually add dry ingredients again; mix well.

title: tomato and artichoke casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add drained whole tomatoes and artichokes.
Add basil; mix.
Do not mash.
Arrange in small buttered casserole and bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until bubbly.
Serves 4.
Nice with meat or fish.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix
soups,
sour
cream and onion.
Layer mixture with potatoes,
starting
with potatoes in baking dish.	Cover with grated
cheese
and
sprinkle with parsley flakes and paprika. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in balls.
Roll in coconut or pecans.

title: tadpole in a hole
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 400°. Crack an egg into a mixing bowl and beat it.
Add undrained corn and half the cheese to the egg.
Mix with a wooden spoon.
Add muffin mix and stir until all ingredients are wet (the batter will be thick).
Pour batter into greased baking dish.
With paper towels, pat sausage links dry.
Push links into batters.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: bacon-wrapped poached eggs
directions: Place bacon strips on rack in shallow roasting pan and bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes.
Remove bacon and drain.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Grease 6 Pyrex custard cups.
Circle inside edge of each cup with bacon.
Break egg into center of each and sprinkle with cheese and salt and pepper if desired.
Bake in 325° oven for 16 minutes or until whites are set but yolks are still soft.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Wash cauliflower, and break into flowerets.
