Cook, covered, in a small amount of boiling water 10 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain.
Place cauliflower in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine milk and tapioca in a heavy saucepan, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in salt and paprika. Add cheese and stir until melted; spoon over cauliflower.
Combine breadcrumbs and butter, stirring well; spoon over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup oleo, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well; spoon into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Crush cornflakes and stir in remaining oleo.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Garnish with lemon twist and parsley, if desired.

title: molasses cupcakes
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar, butter and molasses.
Add the flour, buttermilk, baking soda, ginger and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in greased cupcake pans or use paper liners.

title: rainbow candy(a free treat)
directions: Pour 8 ounces of pop in pan and sprinkle one package gelatin at a time until absorbed.
Add rest of pop gradually.
Stir and let set until gel is completely softened.
Place pan on low heat and stir until all is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add sweetener, flavoring and coloring.
Pour in jelly roll pan 10 x 15-inches. Set in refrigerator 30 minutes covered.
Will be very firm.
Cut in desired shapes.
Will keep in refrigerator one week.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients and shape into balls. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat until creamy. Add one egg at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and cocoa. Alternate flour and milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dressing for mixed fruit
directions: Beat pineapple juice, flour or cornstarch, sugar and egg yolk and cook until thick.
Cool and add to mixed fruit.
Also fold in Dream Whip before serving.

title: 60 minute yeast rolls
directions: In large bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Combine water, milk and butter.
Heat over low heat until very warm, 120° to 130°.
Add to dry ingredients "slowly."
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 1/2 cup flour; beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Stir in additional flour to make soft dough.

title: easy penuche frosting
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat for 2 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Stir in 1/4 cup milk.
Stir until it comes to a boil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add powdered sugar.
Beat until creamy.

title: northwest coast salad dressing
directions: Whip together salmon, egg, mustard, garlic and sugar.
Slowly add alternating oil and vinegar.
Add pepper, cheese and milk; combine thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: In medium saucepan saute onion in margarine until soft.
Blend in flour; cook until smooth and bubbly.
Slowly add milk and broth; bring to boil; add vegetables, salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well with a mixer.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Roll in crushed pecans.
Serve with your choice of crackers.

title: crunchy ham salad
directions: Mix well the ham, apples, celery and nuts.
Cream together the remaining ingredients; pour over ham salad mixture.

title: pita
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and orange juice.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt, then add to butter mixture.
Mix with spoon until it becomes a soft dough. Press about 3/4 dough into an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Spread pie filling over dough.
Dot filling with butter, and sprinkle with ground nuts.
With leftover dough, make pencil thin strips and place around edges, then make lattice strips and put diagonally over entire pita.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until light brown.

title: butterfly pork chops
directions: Cover pork chops with flour and lightly brown in frying pan. Place in baking dish.
Pour chicken soup over pork chops and bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: majestic bars
directions: Stir first 5 items together, mixing well.
Add chips and nuts. Pour into oblong pan or dish which has been coated well with Baker's Joy or Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: Measure 6 cups flour.
Heat milk in small saucepan over low heat until bubbles appear around the edge.
Remove from heat; add butter and salt.
Cool until lukewarm.
Pour warm water into large bowl, sprinkle with yeast and stir until dissolved.
Stir in milk. Add 3 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Gradually stir in just enough of remaining flour to make soft dough, scraping bowl occasionally.
Turn out onto floured board and knead 8 to 10 minutes until dough is smooth and elastic, adding additional flour to board as needed to prevent dough from sticking.
Shape dough into ball and place in greased bowl.
Turn on to bring greased side up.
Cover with a damp cloth and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch down and turn out onto a lightly floured board.
Cover and let rest for 15 minutes.
Divide dough in half and shape into 2 loaves.
Place in 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: italian cheesecake
directions: Mix Ricotta and cream cheese thoroughly and then add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Crust:	Mix flour, nuts and margarine together and pack in bottom of baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: chicken curry with almond-raisin rice
directions: Saute apples, onions and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, seasonings and chicken broth.
Cook over low heat until slightly thickened.
Add chicken and heat until hot.
Serve over Almond-Raisin Rice.
Serves 4 to 6.
"Most delicious."

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon, add onion.
Saute until clear.
Add potato and clam juice.
Cook on medium for 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients. Bring to boil.
Cook on medium for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press into sheet cake pan.
Blend together pecans, coconut, cream cheese, powdered sugar,
eggs and vanilla.
Crumble over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cup cookies(makes 24 to 30 cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together butter, peanut butter and both sugars.
Then beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt to creamed mixture and blend well.

title: caramel pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1 cup sugar.
Mix sugar and egg mixture with flour, margarine and milk in saucepan and slowly cook until begins to thicken.
Meanwhile, brown or melt 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet.
When same temperature, gradually add the sugar to the other mixture.
Put in baked crust.
Beat egg whites and put on pie.
Brown in a 350° oven.

title: company rice
directions: Melt margarine; brown rice with seasonings and onions.
Combine with other ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Pour all ingredients in a bowl, stir well.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased round baking dish.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine 2/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a sack, cut biscuits in quarters and shake in bag.
Put in greased tube pan a few at a time; add nuts.
Mix oleo, 1 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a sauce pan and bring to a boil; boil to bubbly stage. Pour over biscuits after all have been put into the pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Tear apart to serve.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Peel potatoes after cooked.
Grate into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients plus salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours covered or overnight. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Boil and debone chicken, saving broth. Add broth, rice, bread crumbs, pimiento, black olives and eggs. Put in baking dish and spread undiluted mushroom soup over top. Sprinkle slivered almonds on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. After removing from oven, sprinkle oregano on top.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach as per instructions on package, and drain.
Add all ingredients, except bread crumbs, to spinach and cook on low heat.
When cheese melts, add bread crumbs and put in oven at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry wreath for punch
directions: Arrange cherries in bottom of 1 1/4-quart ring mold, alternating color.
Pour on just enough boiling water to cover cherries.
Freeze solid.
Fill mold to top with cold boiled water and freeze again.
Sprigs of mint may be added, if available.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until tender; peel and slice.
Cut bacon slices in halves.
Butter baking dish and alternate potatoes and bacon.
Sprinkle with onion and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and spices and pour over casserole.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.
This can be made up a day ahead of time.

title: bite-size party hot dogs
directions: Cut wieners and bacon in thirds.
Wrap each wiener in bacon and secure with a toothpick.
(There may be more wiener pieces than bacon.)
Layer wieners in crock-pot with brown sugar.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cook slow until tender and lightly brown.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook tortellini as directed on package.
Drain and rinse with cold water and drain well.
Cook artichokes if fresh or frozen. If using marinated artichoke hearts, drain well.
Cut artichoke bottoms into 1/4-inch slivers and artichoke hearts into small pieces.
Combine cooked tortellini, artichokes, pimiento and sweet basil with mayonnaise and mustard.
Season to taste.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add a little more mayonnaise if salad seems dry.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and peppers (hot or plain).
Season meat with garlic, salt and pepper. Drain fat.

title: spiced pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat 2 minutes on medium speed of electric mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool. Combine confectioners sugar and milk.
Stir until smooth. Drizzle over cake.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain chunky fruit.
Drain pineapple and save the juice.
Mix Jell-O pudding and Tang together.
Add pineapple juice to pudding mixture and stir until dissolved.
Pour over fruit and mix gently. Sprinkle bananas with a little lemon juice to prevent discoloration and add to mixture.

title: grandma waits' boiled custard
directions: You take the wite mike and thin you take the sweesey stouf and you sweesit.

title: calypso pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in bowl.
Blend in softened butter.
Put in pie plate and chill 2 hours.
Melt unsweetened chocolate and butter in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 2/3 cup sugar and salt until blended.
Gradually add evaporated milk and blend well.
Return to heat, stirring constantly for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and almond extract.
Cool and chill for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients, except butter and dressing mix.
Put 1/2 bag of dressing mix in bottom of buttered 2-quart casserole, then add the squash mixture.
Top with rest of dressing mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake a 350° for 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix; spray dish with Pam.
Cook on about 250° until done. Sprinkle cheese on top before baking.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Serve with chilled cooked shrimp, lobster or crab or with fresh oysters or clams.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add water and vanilla.
Last, add nuts.
Shape into cocoon-like pieces and bake in a hot oven.
Shake in a sack containing 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm. Add yeast, softened in lukewarm water.
Add egg.
Gradually stir in flour to form soft dough.
Beat vigorously.
Cover and let rise in warm place (80°) until doubled, about 2 hours.
Turn out on floured surface.
Add currants/raisins and cinnamon.
Form in buns and flatten slightly.
Brush top with milk.
Let rise until very light.
Using scissors, snip top of buns at right angles to form cross.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
While hot, brush lightly with confectioners frosting.
Cool, then make cross with more frosting.

title: melton pie
directions: Melt butter; set aside.
Beat 2 eggs and add to butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and coconut.
Beat until smooth.
Add Bisquick; beat again by hand until smooth.
Add meltons and mix.
Pour into 8-inch or 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° or until middle of pie is done after testing with a toothpick.
Cool for at least 1 hour. If using 8-inch pie pan, this will make two pies.
A 9-inch pan will make one.

title: cocoons
directions: Cream butter and 1/3 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Blend flour in gradually.
Add nuts.
Pinch off small quantities and shape into 1 1/2-inch cocoons with palms of hands. Place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until cocoons dry out.
While still warm, roll in remaining 1/3 cup of sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookie wreath(for christmas)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line two 12-inch pizza pans with foil. Invert a custard cup (or 4-inch ovenproof bowl) in center of each pan and grease outside of bowl.
Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Combine the flour, baking soda and salt; stir into the first mixture.
Stir in the chips and nuts.
Spread half of the dough in each pan to within 1/2 inch of bowl and pan edges. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until light golden brown.
Carefully remove bowls; cool and remove from pan.
Decorate as desired.
Put a bow on, put in a box and you've got a neat gift, and it's edible!

title: hi brow walleye
directions: Simmer fish until it flakes with a fork.
Cook onion in butter until clear or tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup milk; stir until thick.
Add cheese; prepare sour cream.
Add fish, mushrooms and peas.
Put in buttered baking dish, crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Very good.

title: mom's goulash
directions: Saute meat, onion and celery in iron skillet.
Add corn and tomatoes.
Add seasonings and noodles.
Top with cheese.
Cover and simmer until cheese melts.
Yummy served with corn bread and green salad.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine beans.
Slowly stir vinegar into sugar, blending until smooth.
Add celery seed, oil and onion.
Refrigerate.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and set aside.
Mix oleo, cream cheese and sugar; set aside.
Mix milk and instant pudding.
Add cheese mixture and blend.
Add topping and blend.
In a clean, plastic flowerpot, layer crushed cookies and filling mixture several times starting and ending with the cookies.
The top will look like potting soil.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Put artificial flower (type depending on season) in center and a child's shovel for serving.

title: cold slaw
directions: Mix the listed ingredients and let set in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: marinated corn salad
directions: Heat sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper. Combine with remaining ingredients and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Crumble and fry 1 pound sausage; drain.
Put in baking dish. Mix all ingredients except cheese together; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Put dry ingredients in mixing bowl and cut in shortening as you would if you were making pie crust.
Add a pinch of salt. Stir in sugar, slightly beaten eggs and flavorings.
Stir together until blended.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Roll out enough for one pan.
Cut out with cookie cutter and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pepper-spice seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; stir to combine. Store in airtight container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place cut up chicken breasts evenly over the bottom of an 11 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix soups and milk; pour over chicken.
Top this mixture with Stove Top stuffing (prepared as directed). Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa and salt together.
Add slightly beaten eggs, butter and vanilla.
Mix.
Add pecans and cook at 350° until done.

title: sausage dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add all ingredients and then pour in crock-pot on low heat until time to serve.

title: strawberry cheese torte
directions: Preheat oven according to cake box.
Bake and cool as directed on box.
Refrigerate layers to make splitting easier.
Split each cake into 2 thin layers.

title: 1 dish chicken and stuffing
directions: Heat oven to 400`.
Make stuffing and put in center of 2-quart dish.
Place chicken breast all around chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Mix soup, milk, parsley and curry powder, pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes or until no longer pink.
Serve with vegetables.
Serves 6.

title: popcorn cake delight
directions: Place popcorn in a large bowl and set aside.
Combine sugar, syrup, water, vinegar and salt in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture reaches hard ball stage (260°). Remove from heat. Add butter, stirring until butter melts.
Pour syrup in a thin stream over popcorn, stirring until popcorn is evenly coated.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Press mixture into a well-greased 6-cup ring mold.
Cool. Unmold on serving plate.

title: the crews selection
directions: Cut large shrimp in half.
Cook mushrooms, green pepper and onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in mushroom soup, cheese and pepper.
Heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Stir in shrimp.
Pour into a well-greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over top of shrimp mixture.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated and crumbs are brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: holiday punch
directions: Dissolve mints in 1 quart hot water.
Mix juice, sugar and mint water together.
Then add enough cracked ice and water to make 3 gallons punch.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
Serve with Bohemian rye uncut round loaf with the inside scooped out.
Use inside portion for dipping.
Also great with vegetables for dipping.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Layer noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and hamburger with sauce.
Cover and cook 8 minutes.
Turn and cook 8 more minutes.

title: roach poison
directions: Mix and sprinkle all around baseboard and in cabinets and in the garage.
It kills roaches but is not poisonous to children or animals.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onions until they lose their color. Drain.
Beat egg; add cottage cheese.
Pour over hamburger and onions in pie crust.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° until set as in custard pie.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Melt the chocolate in an ovenproof dish in microwave on High for 4 minutes (approximately).
Stir in milk, raisins, nuts and salt.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Let candy harden at room temperature.
After top has hardened, turn carefully with knife or spatula and let underside harden.
Simple, quick and delicious.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Cream butter in small mixer bowl.
Add cocoa; blend well. Gradually add powdered sugar, milk and vanilla alternately.
Beat to spreading consistency.
Spread over cooled cake.
Yields 2 cups icing.

title: cherry dream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a medium bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: honey rice custard
directions: Measure milk and water into a saucepan; bring to the boiling point.
Stir in the rice; simmer gently until tender, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
(This may be cooked in a double boiler without stirring, but it takes much longer.)

When the rice is tender, stir in the honey and add some of the hot rice to the egg yolks and stir thoroughly, then stir the yolks into the rice. Turn into the serving dish, sprinkled with cinnamon and nutmeg. Serve very cold.
This is delicious with stewed dried fruit.

title: fresh banana pie
directions: Fill cup with sugar and pour juice of lemon over sugar and let stand until sugar absorbs juice.
Cut bananas to fill shell.
Pour sugar juice mixture over bananas.
Cover with whipped cream.
Serve immediately.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage until tender.
Drain off all liquid, reserving 1/2 cup.
Alternate cabbage with layer of cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Top with 1 can soup that has been diluted with 1/2 cup reserved liquid.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar, salt and vanilla in bowl and mix well with mixer.
Add fruit if desired and blend in.

title: farm chicken
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Season the chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown both sides in heated oil.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic to skillet; cook until softened, about 5 minutes.
Return chicken to pan; cover and cook on medium-low for approximately 45 to 50 minutes, stirring often.
Gently stir in frozen peas; cook for another 5 minutes. Serve with potatoes, rice or noodles.
If too dry, add chicken broth.
Serves 4.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Saute onions and brown meat.
Mix in the tomato soup and water. Add the cooked noodles, corn and cheese.
Mix well and cook at 350° for 45 minutes in a covered dish.

title: lentil soup(serves 6)
directions: Continue to cook on medium heat 30 to 40 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Contains 99 calories per bowl.

title: turkey, broccoli, noodle bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and noodles.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over broccoli and noodles.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Pound the cutlets lightly; salt and then dip first in egg and then in breadcrumbs.
Fry on both sides in hot oil until brown. Time:
Pork cutlets, 10 to 15 minutes; veal or chicken, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: Cut ends off cucumbers; fork down sides.
Slice very thin. Layer slices in glass bowl, generously salting each layer, until bowl is full.
Press down with lid or plate.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, pour off brine and toss with about 1 pint sour cream.
Serve cold.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms (do not rinse).
Remove stems and chop to make 1 cup. Cook with onions in butter until tender. Stir in flour, savory and pepper. Add broth and 2 teaspoons water. Cook until thick and bubbly.
Stir in bacon, cheese and bread crumbs. Fill caps. Sprinkle with parsley and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick goulash
directions: In a 5-quart pan, place 6 cups of water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil.
Add macaroni and cook until tender.
Drain and reserve.
In same pan, brown ground beef and drain off grease. Add macaroni to beef.
Stir and add tomato juice.
Warm through on medium heat.
Stir occasionally.
Season to taste.

title: sausage broccoli soup
directions: Brown, crumble and drain sausage.
Cook vegetables in chicken broth.
Cook tortellini.
Combine all ingredients; heat and serve. Sprinkle with grated Romano cheese (optional).

title: taco hamburgers
directions: Mix
ingredients
well and make into hamburger patties. Cook until well done.

title: microwave bean dip
directions: Mix beans and sauce in a microwave-safe bowl and heat 2 minutes on High, stirring every 30 seconds.
Spread mixture into a shallow dish and cover with reserved sauce.
Top with sour cream, cheese and vegetables.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Break up sausage into small pieces.
Allow to stand at room temperature until softened.
Mix in cheese and Bisquick mix with hands.
Thoroughly blend the mixture until it can be formed into a large ball.

Pinch off small pieces and roll into little balls. Place on baking sheet and bake in preheated oven at 325° to 350° for about 20 minutes or until balls are puffed and golden brown. They should be baked on a rack one notch below the middle of oven. Serve with mustard or chili sauce.
Recipe makes about 100.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and stir in cornmeal.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Beat until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can double the recipe and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake a little longer.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute next three ingredients in medium pan.
Over low heat, stir in soup until well mixed.
Add cheese and heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: new england clam chowder and scallops
directions: Tip:
Three 5 or 6 ounce cans of chopped clams in juice may be used instead of fresh clams.

title: stir crazy cake
directions: Put flour, 1 1/2 Cups sugar, cocoa, soda and salt into an ungreased 13 X 9 X 2 inch metal baking pan.
Stir with a fork to mix; form 3 wells in flour mixture.
Pour oil in one, vinegar in one and vanilla in the other.
Pour cold coffee over all ingredients and stir with fork until well mixed.
Do not beat. Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon, sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350 for 35-49 minutes.

title: mexican beans
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot on high until boiling and then reduce to low. When beans are ready, add chopped onion, tomato, fried bacon and cilantro.

title: pork chop spanish rice
directions: Trim excess fat from each pork chop.
Slowly brown chops in melted shortening, about 15 to 20 minutes; drain off excess fat. Combine salt, cumin, chili powder and pepper; sprinkle over chops. Add rice, onion and chopped green pepper.
Pour tomatoes over top. Cover and cook over low heat 35 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add green pepper rings and cook 5 minutes longer or until rice and meat are tender.
Serves 5.

title: chutney cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Finely chop green onions, stems included.
Add curry, mustard and chutney.
Refrigerate until firm (can freeze if you are in a hurry).
Roll in chopped pecans when firm.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: light and moist banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour two 9 x 5 loaf pans. In a large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients. Stir in nuts and set aside.

title: macaroni cheese pie
directions: Cook macaroni and drain well. Grate 1/2 pound cheese into buttered casserole dish. Put in half the macaroni. Dot with butter. Add onion. Sprinkle with grated cheese (use half for each layer). Add another layer of macaroni, butter, onion, salt, pepper and cheese. Cover with bacon. Bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Stir into a cream mixture.
Make about 5 dozen small cookies.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Roll out cookies, place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: scallop chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Remove skin and bones.
Set aside. Mix onion, celery and stuffing with this.
Make layer in a baking pan, then a layer of chicken meat.
Alternate layers until all meat and stuffing are used.
Bring broth to a boil.
Using at least 1 quart, pour over mixture. Bake 45 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix all together and bake (uncovered) 45 minutes at 275°. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Wash and skin chicken.
Dilute lemon juice 50/50 with water. Cover chicken and let marinate for several hours in the refrigerator.
(Add a dash of lime juice.)
Take chicken from marinade and evenly salt, powder and apply crumbs.
It's important to season around all sides of chicken.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Heat margarine, sour cream, cheese, onion, soup and ranch dressing mix.
Blend well and pour over shredded potatoes.
Pour 1/2 cup milk over potatoes.
Top with 3/4 cup cornflakes mixed with 2 TBSP. margarine, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Can add bacon bits to casserole if desired.

title: grandma emily's sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, eggs, oil and butter together.
Add dry ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Roll in balls and flatten with a glass or cut out shapes.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry-cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Measure flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and peel into bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add water to juice to measure 3/4 cup; mix in with cheese and egg.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into pan. Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan; let loaf stand at least 8 hours.
Makes 18 slices.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour sugar and cornstarch in a bowl. Add eggs and beat.
Add milk, salt, butter and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until set firm.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown the hamburg and onions.
Mix brown sugar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika, mustard and vinegar water.
Add to hamburg. Simmer a little.
Add a little flour to thicken.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Butter 2 large cookie sheets.
In heavy saucepan stir together sugar, salt, allspice, cinnamon, water and syrup.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until boiling.

Continue cooking over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until it reaches 235° on a candy thermometer or until mixture forms a soft ball in water. Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts, stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Working quickly with a small metal spatula, drop each coated pecan half well apart onto cookie sheets.
Cool completely. Store in airtight containers.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and nutmeg and pour together in a large bowl. Add the eggs, slightly beaten, along with the vanilla and sour cream. Mix the dry ingredients well with the liquid ingredients and then add the rhubarb and fold together. Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. Turn oven down to 350° and bake for an additional 30 to 40 minutes until it is set.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple, bananas, nuts and undrained strawberries.
Turn 1/2 of the mixture into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over firm gelatin. Spoon remaining gelatin which has been kept at room temperature over the sour cream.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate angel meringues
directions: Beat egg whites with a pinch of salt and cream of tartar until foamy.
Add sugar gradually until stiff peaks hold.
Fold in nuts and vanilla. Drop in mounds on brown paper covered cookie sheets, hollowing out the middles and building up the sides.
(May be spread in greased 9-inch pie pan building up sides 1/2-inch above edge of pan.) Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool and fill with Chocolate Cream.

title: devil dogs
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Add milk, vanilla, flour and cocoa.
Dissolve the soda in hot water and add to mixture.
Beat and then drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 4 to 6 minutes.

title: pork picata
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small bowl.
Dredge pork in flour mixture.
Coat a large skillet with oil.
Add pork and cook 4 to 5 minutes on each side, until browned.
Transfer to platter and keep warm.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll sugar cookie dough on 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (or until light brown).
Let cool completely.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together cake mix, pie filling and eggs in large mixer bowl.
Beat 2 minutes.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Spread half the batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Repeat with remaining batter and cinnamon-sugar.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool.

title: ambrosia
directions: *May use other citrus fruit.

title: oreo smush dessert
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and melted oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving a small amount for topping.
Press evenly in bottom of pan.
Layer ice cream, fudge sauce, Cool Whip and reserved crumbs over crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape into balls.
Roll in flaked coconut and place in sealed container in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the chocolate chips.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 1/2 hour, then unmold and dust with powdered sugar.

title: snickers cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour half of mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix caramels, margarine and milk.
Pour this over baked crust.
Sprinkle chips and nuts on this.
Pour the rest of the batter on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° and then 10 minutes at 325°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together the graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted butter.
Spread in bottom of oblong pan.
Mix together well the powdered sugar, 2 sticks soft butter, eggs and vanilla.
Beat for 20 minutes.
Spread over cracker crumbs.
Spread the pineapple (drained) over the filling.
Slice the bananas in pineapple juice and lay over pineapple layer.
Spread Cool Whip over the bananas. Top with 1 jar maraschino cherries and the nuts.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Cream all, mixing together.
Pour in jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: old fashioned banana pudding(`the real mccoy')
directions: Mix together and pour in boiler and cook slowly until mixture thickens.
Stir constantly while cooking.

title: meal in one
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and onions.
Pour off fat.
Add soups, water, pepper, beans and carrots.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish, spoon potatoes in diagonal lines across top of casserole. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Combine shortening and sugars in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients.
Add to eggs and sugar/shortening mixture, blending well.
Stir in 1/2 cup of candies.
Save rest for decorating tops of cookies.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with candy.
Bake in 375° oven 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely. This recipe can be doubled.
Store in airtight containers.

title: popcorn cake(fun with children)
directions: Spray large tube cake pan or large bowl with Pam.
Melt marshmallows, margarine and oil.
Combine all other ingredients in large bowl.
Pour marshmallow mixture over and mix well.
Spoon into pan or leave in large bowl.
Let sit for ten to fifteen minutes to cool and mold.
Invert container onto serving platter and slice.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Remove all unpopped kernels and place popped corn in a large roasting pan in oven.
Keep warm in oven at 300°.
Butter sides of a 2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar, water, corn syrup, vinegar and salt in buttered saucepan.
Cook on stove top to a soft crack stage, stirring frequently (mixture should boil gently).
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture over warm popcorn. Stir gently until mixed.
Butter hands and use a butter coated cup to shape into 3-inch balls.
Let cool!
Yields 13 to 15 (3-inch) balls.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes or until top is browned.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add margarine and sugar and mix well.
Beat in the egg and add to flour.
Put in airtight container and refrigerate 4 hours.
Grease muffin pan and spoon in rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: french apple pie
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Mix lightly through sliced apples. Heap up in pastry lined pan.
Dot with 1 1/2 tablespoons butter. Mix 1/2 cup butter, brown sugar and flour.
Sprinkle on top of pie and bake until apples are tender.

title: gingered chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in microwavable 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with the thickest part to the outside edge with skin side down (if pieces have skin on).
Mix honey, chili sauce, soy sauce, ginger, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High (100%) for 10 minutes.
Spoon sauce over chicken. Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Cover and microwave until thickest parts are done, 7 to 11 minutes longer.
Remove chicken from pan and keep warm.
Skin fat from sauce.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir into sauce and microwave uncovered on High (100%), stirring every minute until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Pour over chicken.

title: mushroom caps
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; reserve.
Simmer mushroom caps and stems in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Drain; invert caps on a paper towel.
Cool.
Chop enough stems to make 2/3 cup (save remainder for other use).
Combine cheese and dry dressing mix; stir in nuts, chopped stems and crumbled bacon.
Spoon into caps; place in a shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Bake in a 425° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: rosamarina
directions: Cook macaroni, as directed on box.
Drain fruit, reserving juice.
Cook juice, eggs, sugar, salt and flour in saucepan until consistency of pudding.
Pour over macaroni.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Then add fruit, and fold in Cool Whip. Very Good!

title: mom's cucumber slaw
directions: Slice onions and cucumbers.
Sprinkle with salt and let set for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Liquid will form and then squeeze out liquid. Use pepper and vinegar to taste, usually 1/3 part vinegar to 1 part water, depending on strength of vinegar.
Add water later if necessary.

title: down east clam bake
directions: Wash and scrub clams until clean, grit free.
Place clams in shell on bottom of large steamer or canning pot.
Pour in water. Add potatoes, onions, chicken breasts, carrots and corn in order given.
Cover pot and bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat but maintain the boil.
Food steams and cooks in 1 hour.
If sweet potato is tender, all is done.
Put shrimp in during last 30 minutes.
Watch to see that water does not cook out.
To serve, place pot in middle of table.
Place each ingredient on each plate and let clam lovers remove as many clams and liquid as they desire. Crust corn bread goes well with the clam bake.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon and onion in medium skillet until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Pour beans into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in bacon and onion, syrup, catsup, mustard and pepper sauce until well mixed.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until beans are hot and bubbly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix.
Form into small round balls.
Press with fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ruth's bread
directions: Combine 2 teaspoons sugar, 1 cup warm water and dry yeast; let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Combine 4 cups warm water, sugar, salt and vegetable oil.
Add yeast mixture.
Add flour and knead.
Let rise.
Knead again.
Put in pans and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes

title: sausage casserole(breakfast casserole)
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and dried mustard.
Place sausage in bottom of a casserole dish and spread layer of bread cubes and shredded cheese on top.
Pour egg mixture on top; cover.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven.
Yields 1 dozen muffins.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Brown meat and onion in skillet. Combine all ingredients except cheese in a large bowl.
Put mixture in casserole dish and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted. Yields 8 servings.

title: singerport sling
directions: Mix all together, makes 2 fifths and 1 pint.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all except pecans.
Cover and chill overnight.
Shape into a ball; roll in pecans.

title: russian salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a quart jar.
Place lid on and shake 2 minutes.
Keep refrigerated.
